AGRO:00000017.label: conservation tillage process
AGRO:00000017.definition: A tillage process in which a proportion of plant residue, left over after a harvesting process, is left relatively undisturbed on the tilled land; this is done in order to accomplish several conservation objectives including the maintenance of soil moisture content, the reduction of soil erosion and soil compaction, and/or the reduction of labour intensity and fuel consumption.

AGRO:00000015.label: conventional tillage process
AGRO:00000015.definition: A tillage process in which, approximately, less than 15 percent of the soil surface is covered by crop residue after planting.

AGRO:00000028.label: puddling process
AGRO:00000028.definition: A tillage process in which saturated or near-saturated soil are worked into soft structureless mud, mainly for paddy rice production.

AGRO:00000016.label: reduced tillage process
AGRO:00000016.definition: A tillage process in which between, approximately, 15 to 30 percent of the soil surface is covered by plant residue after planting.

AGRO:00000020.label: laser land levelling process
AGRO:00000020.definition: A land levelling process in which a laser guided equipement is used to shape land surface.

AGRO:00000214.label: traditional land levelling process
AGRO:00000214.definition: A land levelling process which uses animal drawn or tractor-drawn levelers.

AGRO:00000212.label: crop residue burning process
AGRO:00000212.definition: A crop residue management process in which crop residues are burned in the field.

AGRO:00000213.label: crop residue spreading process
AGRO:00000213.definition: A crop residue management process in which crop residues are spread across the field.

AGRO:01000015.label: tillage
AGRO:01000015.definition: group together tillage and no-till processes

AGRO:00000055.label: localized irrigation process
AGRO:00000055.definition: An irrigation process in which water is distributed under low pressure through a piped network, and is applied as a small discharge to each plant or adjacent to it.

AGRO:00000060.label: sprinkler irrigation process
AGRO:00000060.definition: An irrigation process in which water is distributed through a system of pipes, and is sprayed into the air through sprinklers so that it breaks up into small water drops which fall to the ground.

AGRO:00000062.label: sub-irrigation process
AGRO:00000062.definition: An irrigation process in which water is delivered to the plant root zone from below the soil surface.

AGRO:00000063.label: surface irrigation process
AGRO:00000063.definition: An irrigation process in which water is applied and distributed over the soil surface by gravity.

ENVO:00000020.label: lake
ENVO:00000020.definition: A body of water or other liquid of considerable size contained on a body of land.

ENVO:00000022.label: river
ENVO:00000022.definition: A stream which, through permanent or seasonal flow processes, moves from elevated land towards lower elevations through a definite channel and empties either into a sea, lake, or another river or ends on land as bed seepage and evapotranspiration exceed water supply.

ENVO:00000027.label: spring
ENVO:00000027.definition: A point where groundwater or steam flows out of the ground, and is thus where the aquifer surface meets the ground surface or where there is a fissure.

AGRO:00000029.label: mulch-till
AGRO:00000029.definition: A conservation tillage process in which non-inversion tillage tools that partially incorporate surface organic material are used on the entire surface of the field.

AGRO:00000030.label: ridge-till
AGRO:00000030.definition: A conservation tillage process in which, in a land with permanent ridges, previous crop's residue is cleared off ridge-tops into adjacent furrows to make way for the new crop being planted on ridges.

AGRO:00000031.label: strip-till
AGRO:00000031.definition: A conservation tillage process in which narrow strips are tilled where seeds will be planted, leaving the soil in between the rows untilled.

AGRO:00000108.label: mechanical pest destruction process
AGRO:00000108.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which pests are killed.

AGRO:00000109.label: mechanical pest exclusion process
AGRO:00000109.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which pests are kept away.

AGRO:00000110.label: mechanical pest removal process
AGRO:00000110.synonyms: removal technique;A mechanical pest control process in which pests are removed without being killed.

AGRO:00000106.label: organisms augmentation process
AGRO:00000106.definition: A biological pest control process in which organisms that help to manage pests are released to boost the naturally occurring population.

AGRO:00000107.label: organisms conservation process
AGRO:00000107.definition: A biological pest control process in which suitable habitat or food are provided to the naturally occurring population of organisms that help to manage pests.

AGRO:00000105.label: organisms importation process
AGRO:00000105.definition: A biological pest control process in which organisms that will help to manage pests are introduced to a new locale where they do not occur naturally.

AGRO:00000022.label: biological pest control process
AGRO:00000022.definition: A pest control process in which organisms are employed to manage unwanted organisms.

AGRO:00000024.label: chemical pest control process
AGRO:00000024.definition: A pest control process in which chemical is used to manage unwanted organisms.

AGRO:00000021.label: mechanical pest control process
AGRO:00000021.definition: A pest control process in which physical means such as barriers, traps and handpicking, or physical conditions like high temperature, are used to control unwanted organisms.

AGRO:00000454.label: threshing process
AGRO:00000454.definition: Planned process is which the edible part of the cereal grain is loosen from the scaly, inedible chaff that surrounds it. It is the step in grain preparation after harvesting and before winnowing, which separates the loosened chaff from the grain. Threshing does not remove the bran from the grain.

AGRO:00000457.label: winnowing process
AGRO:00000457.definition: A planned process in which the grain is separated from chaff. It is also used to remove weevils or other pests from stored grain. It is done after threshing, the loosening of grain or seeds from the husks and straw.

AGRO:00000007.label: desuckering process
AGRO:00000007.definition: A pruning process in which one or more suckers are removed.

AGRO:00000459.label: detrashing process
AGRO:00000459.definition: A pruning process in which dried, yellowish green, bottom leaves in the sugarcane crop are removed at regular intervals.

AGRO:00000458.label: tree topping process
AGRO:00000458.definition: A pruning process in which whole tops of trees or large branches and/or trunks from the tops of trees are removed, leaving stubs or lateral branches that are too small to assume the role of a terminal leader.

PO:0009010.label: seed
PO:0009010.definition: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a plant ovule (PO:0020003) and has as parts a plant embryo (PO:0009009) enclosed in a seed coat (PO:0009088).

PO:0000003.label: whole plant
PO:0000003.definition: A plant structure (PO:0005679) which is a whole organism.

AGRO:00000114.label: plant cutting
AGRO:00000114.definition: Piece of a plant, often piece of the stem or root, that is used for vegetative propagation.

AGRO:00000113.label: pregerminated seed
AGRO:00000113.definition: Seed soaked in water until the physical process of germination, the penetration of the root though the seed coat, has occurred.

AGRO:00000115.label: ratoon
AGRO:00000115.definition: A shoot of a perennial plant.

AGRO:00000037.label: aerial application
AGRO:00000037.definition: An application method in which a liquid material entity is applied by aircraft to an area.

AGRO:00000038.label: band application
AGRO:00000038.definition: An application method in which a material entity is applied in bands below, above, on one side, or on both sides of seeds or seedlings at planting.

AGRO:00000040.label: broadcast application method
AGRO:00000040.definition: An application method which specifies how a material entity is to be uniformly applied to an area.

AGRO:00000043.label: chemical basal application
AGRO:00000043.definition: An application method in which a chemical entity is applied to the lower portions of plant stems or tree trunks just above the soil line.

AGRO:00000044.label: chemigation
AGRO:00000044.definition: An application method in which a water-soluble chemical is injected into water flowing through an irrigation system.

AGRO:00000045.label: contact placement
AGRO:00000045.definition: An application method in which a material entity is applied at the time of sowing, and placed in contact with seeds.
AGRO:00000045.synonyms: combined drilling;drill placement;placed with seed application;pop-up application;on the seed application;seed placement

AGRO:00000046.label: deep placement
AGRO:00000046.definition: An application method in which the material entity is placed in the reduced soil layer.

AGRO:00000412.label: dibbling
AGRO:00000412.definition: An application method in which a material entity is placed into the soil in holes made with a pointed implement.

AGRO:00000413.label: drilling
AGRO:00000413.definition: An application method in which seeds are uniformlyplaced into shallow furrows before closing the furrows.

AGRO:00000047.label: fertigation
AGRO:00000047.definition: An application method in which a water-soluble fertilizer is injected into water flowing through an irrigation system.

AGRO:00000048.label: foliar application
AGRO:00000048.definition: An application method in which a liquid material entity is sprayed to the leafy portions of a plant.

AGRO:00000049.label: plough sole placement
AGRO:00000049.definition: An application method in which the material entity is placed in a continuous band on the bottom of the furrow during the process of ploughing. Each band is covered as the next furrow is turned. The aim is to place the material entity in moist soil where it can become more available to growing plants.

AGRO:00000050.label: rope-wick application
AGRO:00000050.definition: An application method in which a liquid material entity is conveyed from a reservoir to a rope or wick that is wiped into unwanted plants.

AGRO:00000051.label: seed dressing
AGRO:00000051.definition: An application method in which a material entity is appplied directly on seeds before seeding.

AGRO:00000052.label: soil injection
AGRO:00000052.definition: An application method in which a material entity is injected under pressure beneath the soil surface.

AGRO:00000053.label: tree injection
AGRO:00000053.definition: An application method in which a material entity is injected under the bark of trees.

AGRO:00000039.label: side dressing
AGRO:00000039.definition: A band application in which the material entity is applied after seeding or planting.

AGRO:00000041.label: fertilizer basal application
AGRO:00000041.definition: A broadcast application in which fertilizer is applied to an area before planting or before seedling emergence.

AGRO:00000042.label: top dressing
AGRO:00000042.definition: A broadcast application in which a material entity is applied to an area after seedling emergence and establishment of plants.

AGRO:00000409.label: automatic irrigation
AGRO:00000409.definition: Irrigation method with no or just a minimum of manual intervention beside the surveillance. Almost every system can be automated with help of timers, sensors or computers or mechanical appliances.

AGRO:00000408.label: manual irrigation
AGRO:00000408.definition: Irrigation method based on manual intervention.

AGRO:00000056.label: drip irrigation process
AGRO:00000056.definition: A localized irrigation process in which water is conveyed under pressure through a pipe system where it drips slowly onto the soil close to the plants.

AGRO:00000057.label: pitcher irrigation process
AGRO:00000057.definition: A localized irrigation process in which water is distributed by diffusion and capillary action through the wall of buried unglazed clay pot.

AGRO:00000058.label: subsurface drip irrigation process
AGRO:00000058.definition: A localized irrigation process in which water is conveyed under pressure through a buried pipe system where it drips slowly below the soil surface close to plants' roots.

AGRO:00000059.label: subsurface textile irrigation process
AGRO:00000059.synonyms: An irrigation process in which water is distributed through a buried piped network with a layer of geotextile on top. Geotextiles absorb the water from the drippers of the piped network and transport that water under the soil surface via mass flow and capillary action.;SSTI;subsurface textile irrigation

AGRO:00000061.label: center-pivot irrigation process
AGRO:00000061.definition: A sprinkler irrigation process in which water is dispersed through a long, segmented arm that revolves around a pivot point and covers a circular area.
AGRO:00000061.synonyms: circle irrigation;center-pivot irrigation;waterwheel irrigation;central pivot irrigation

AGRO:00000064.label: bassin irrigation process
AGRO:00000064.definition: A surface irrigation process in which water is applied into basins. Basins are flat areas of land surronded by low bunds.

AGRO:00000066.label: border irrigation process
AGRO:00000066.definition: A surface irrigation process in which water is distributed to an area divided into borders. Borders are long, sloping strips of land separated by bunds. Water is applied to the top end of borders.
AGRO:00000066.synonyms: border strip irrigation;border check irrigation;border irrigation;bay irrigation

AGRO:00000067.label: furrow irrigation process
AGRO:00000067.definition: A surface irrigation process in which water is carried into small channels called furrows down the land slope between the plant rows. Water is applied to the top end of each furrow and infiltrates into the soil as it moves along the slope channel.

AGRO:00000068.label: uncontrolled flooding process
AGRO:00000068.definition: A surface irrigation process in which water is spread over a flat area without control over water flow or prior preparation.

AGRO:00000065.label: continuous flood process
AGRO:00000065.definition: A bassin irrigation process in which basins are flooded during the entire growing season of plants.

AGRO:00000077.label: farm slurry
AGRO:00000077.definition: An animal manure made of animal feces and urine with no or very little material used for animal bedding.

AGRO:00000076.label: farmyard manure
AGRO:00000076.definition: Animal manure that contains plant material, which has been used as bedding for animals and has absorbed the feces and urine.

AGRO:00000082.label: fish emulsion
AGRO:00000082.definition: An animal manure that is produced from ground-up whole fish or by-products mixed with water, and heated to remove oils and proteins.

AGRO:00000084.label: fish hydrolysate
AGRO:00000084.definition: An animal manure made from whole fish or by-products put into water and cold-ground up.

AGRO:00000081.label: fish manure
AGRO:00000081.definition: An animal manure that contains solid waste from fishes often originateing from aquaculture operations.

AGRO:00000083.label: fish meal
AGRO:00000083.definition: An animal manure obtained by drying and grinding or otherwise treating fish or fish waste to which no other matter has been added.

AGRO:00000078.label: liquid manure
AGRO:00000078.definition: An animal manure made of animal urine and sometimes waste water.

AGRO:00000080.label: poultry litter
AGRO:00000080.definition: An animal manure that contains poultry excreta, spilled feed, feathers, and material used as bedding in poultry operations.

AGRO:00000089.label: cottonseed meal
AGRO:00000089.definition: An oil meal that contains crushed cotton seeds from which oil has been removed.

AGRO:00000099.label: aluminum mulch
AGRO:00000099.definition: A mulch where foil is used to cover soil surface.

AGRO:00000104.label: bark mulch
AGRO:00000104.definition: A mulch where the outer corky bark layer of timber trees, shredded or not, are used to cover soil surface.

AGRO:00000102.label: compost mulch
AGRO:00000102.definition: A mulch where compost is used to cover soil surface.

AGRO:00000096.label: grass clippings mulch
AGRO:00000096.definition: A mulch where lawn waste resulting from mowing are used to cover the soil surface.

AGRO:00000094.label: landscape fabric
AGRO:00000094.definition: A mulch where textile material is used to covert the soil surface. The fabric itself can be made from synthetic or organic materials, sometimes from recycled sources.

AGRO:00000101.label: leave mulch
AGRO:00000101.definition: A mulch where tree leaves are used to cover soil surface.

AGRO:00000095.label: paper mulch
AGRO:00000095.definition: A mulch where shredded or entire piece of paper or newspaper cover the soil surface.

AGRO:00000097.label: pine needles mulch
AGRO:00000097.definition: A mulch where pine needles are used to cover soil surface.

AGRO:00000093.label: plastic mulch
AGRO:00000093.definition: A mulch where plastic sheet is used to cover soil surface. Plants grow through slits or holes in thin plastic sheeting.

AGRO:00000100.label: stone mulch
AGRO:00000100.definition: A mulch where stones are used to cover soil surface.

AGRO:00000098.label: straw mulch
AGRO:00000098.definition: A mulch where straw is used to cover soil surface.

AGRO:00000103.label: wood chips mulch
AGRO:00000103.definition: A mulch where wood chips are used to cover soil surface. Wood chips are a byproduct of the pruning of trees.

AGRO:00000206.label: cold treatment
AGRO:00000206.definition: A pest control process in which extremely cold temperature are used to kill pest.

AGRO:00000211.label: diatomaceous earth spreading
AGRO:00000211.definition: A mechanical pest process in which diatomaceous earth is used to kill pest. Diatomaceous earth is composed of finely ground skeletons of fossil diatoms. Sharp edges of the ground diatoms scratch the waxy or oily outer layer of soft-bodied insects, which die eventually from dehydration.

AGRO:00000209.label: fire treatment
AGRO:00000209.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which pest or area with pest are directly burned and flamed.

AGRO:00000207.label: flood treatment
AGRO:00000207.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which the area being treated against pest is saturated with water at a depth of 15 to 30 cm for a period of 3 to 8 weeks.

AGRO:00000204.label: heat treatment
AGRO:00000204.definition: A pest control process in wich extremely hot temperature are used to kill pest.

AGRO:00000208.label: soil solarization treatment
AGRO:00000208.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which the soil is covered with a layer of clear or black plastic. The plastic that is covering the ground traps heat energy from the sun and raises the temperature of the soil killing pest.

AGRO:00000210.label: steam treatment
AGRO:00000210.definition: A mechanical pest control process in which steam is used to kill pest.

AGRO:00000002.label: tillage process
AGRO:00000002.definition: A planned process in which soil is mechanicaly mixed, stirred or overturned.

AGRO:00000111.label: mulching process
AGRO:00000111.definition: A planned process in which a layer of material is apply to the soil surface to conserve moisture, improve soil fertility, reduce pests population and enhance the visual appeal of the area.

AGRO:00000216.label: using barrier process
AGRO:00000216.definition: A mechanical pest exclusion process in which barriers are used to prevent pest from getting into the area to be protected.

AGRO:00000217.label: hand picking process
AGRO:00000217.definition: A mechanical pest removal process in which unwanted organisms are removed by hands.

AGRO:00000219.label: insect vacuuming process
AGRO:00000219.definition: A mechanical pest removal process in which a field vacuum is used to suck insects from plants.

AGRO:00000220.label: mowing process
AGRO:00000220.definition: A cutting process in which the above ground of the plants are cut or shred. It can be used to reduce weed seed populations or restrict the growth of weeds.

AGRO:00000215.label: trapping process
AGRO:00000215.definition: A mechanical pest removal process in which pests are physically caught.

AGRO:00000218.label: water pressure spraying process
AGRO:00000218.definition: A mechanical pest removal process in which a forceful stream of water is used to dislodge pests.

AGRO:00000125.label: single-axle tractor
AGRO:00000125.definition: A tractor with one axle, self-powered and self-propelled. The operator usually walks behind it or rides the implement being towed.

AGRO:00000126.label: two-axle tractor
AGRO:00000126.definition: A tractor with two axles. Agricultural implements may be towed behind or mounted on the tractor, and the tractor may also provide a source of power if the implement is mechanized.

AGRO:00000395.label: offset disc harrow
AGRO:00000395.definition: A disk harrow with disc blades arranged into two sections.

AGRO:00000394.label: tandem disc harrow
AGRO:00000394.definition: A disk harrow with disc blades arranged into four sections.

AGRO:00000233.label: chemical pest control implement
AGRO:00000233.definition: An implement that is used during a chemical pest control process.

PATO:0000317.label: black
PATO:0000317.definition: A color that lacks any hues as parts.

PATO:0000952.label: brown
PATO:0000952.definition: A color consisting of dark orange, red, of very low intensity.

PATO:0000950.label: grey
PATO:0000950.definition: A color between white and black colors.

PATO:0000964.label: transparent
PATO:0000964.definition: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking opacity.

PATO:0000323.label: white
PATO:0000323.definition: An achromatic color of maximum brightness; the color of objects that reflect nearly all light of all visible wavelengths.

PATO:0000324.label: yellow
PATO:0000324.definition: A color hue with medium wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between orange and green, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 570 to 590 nanometers.

CHEBI:31344.label: calcium oxide
CHEBI:31344.definition: A member of the class of calcium oxides of calcium and oxygen in a 1:1 ratio.

ENVO:00002053.label: limestone
ENVO:00002053.definition: A sedimentary rock composed largely of the mineral calcite.

ENVO:00002044.label: sludge
ENVO:00002044.definition: The residual semi-solid material left from domestic or industrial processes, or wastewater treatment processes.

AGRO:00000423.label: fertilizer area density over a cropping season
AGRO:00000423.definition: Total quantity of fertilizer applied in a given surface area during a cropping season.

AGRO:00000202.label: seeding area density
AGRO:00000202.definition: An area density quality which inheres in seeds by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of the seeds sown on a given surface area.

AGRO:00000131.label: chisel plough
AGRO:00000131.definition: An implement that loosen and aerate soil without inverting or turning it.

AGRO:00000127.label: clod crusher
AGRO:00000127.definition: A roller armed with blunt spikes for dragging over newly plowed land to break the clods and render it fit for seeding.

AGRO:00000393.label: cultivator
AGRO:00000393.definition: Tillage tool that stirs and pulverizes the soil, either before planting (to aerate the soil and prepare a smooth, loose seedbed) or after the crop has begun growing (to kill weeds—controlled disturbance of the topsoil close to the crop plants kills the surrounding weeds by uprooting them, burying their leaves to disrupt their photosynthesis, or a combination of both). Cultivator is designed to disturb the soil in careful patterns, sparing the crop plants but disrupting the weeds. Cultivator teeth work near the surface.

AGRO:00000128.label: disk harrow
AGRO:00000128.definition: An implement that consists of many carbon steel or boron discs, which have many varying concavities and disc blade sizes and spacing and which are arranged into two or four sections. It is used to till the soil where crops are to be planted. It is also used to chop up unwanted weeds or crop remainders.

AGRO:00000383.label: hand plough
AGRO:00000383.definition: An object to be used by hand to plough soil.

AGRO:00000129.label: mouldboard plough
AGRO:00000129.definition: An implement that cut, lift and reverse soil with a cutting depth of approximately 15 cm.

AGRO:00000392.label: paraplough
AGRO:00000392.definition: Tool for loosening compacted soil layers 12 to 16 inches (30 to 40 cm) deep and still maintain high surface residue levels.

AGRO:00000235.label: puddling implement
AGRO:00000235.definition: An implement that is used during a puddling process.

AGRO:00000132.label: ridging plough
AGRO:00000132.definition: An implement that is used for plants, such as potatoes or scallions, which are grown buried in ridges of soil. A ridging plough has two mouldboards facing away from each other, cutting a deep furrow on each pass, with high ridges either side.

AGRO:00000133.label: spade plough
AGRO:00000133.definition: An implement that is designed to cut the soil and turn it on its side, minimizing the damage to the earthworms, soil microorganism, and fungi.

AGRO:00000130.label: subsoiler
AGRO:00000130.definition: An implement that typically has only one thin blade with a sharpened tip, and is used to loosen and break up soil at depths about 30 cm.

AGRO:00000137.label: chain harrow
AGRO:00000137.definition: An implement consisting of a heavy framework having high numbers of steel tines on an harrow mat.

AGRO:00000136.label: laser-controlled bucket
AGRO:00000136.definition: A bucket tracted by a tractor and controlled by a laser to shape soil surface. A laser transmitter transmits a laser beam, which is intercepted by the laser receiver mounted on the leveling bucket. The control panel mounted on the tractor interprets the signal from the receiver and raises or lowers the bucket.

AGRO:00000134.label: levelling board
AGRO:00000134.definition: Board used in field with a total water coverage to shape field surface. Weight can be added to the board.

AGRO:00000135.label: levelling bucket
AGRO:00000135.definition: Bucket dragged by animal or tractor to shape soil surface. Bucket dimensions and capacity vary according to the available power source and field conditions.

AGRO:00000138.label: tine harrow
AGRO:00000138.definition: An implement consisting of a heavy framework having several spikes or tines, and dragged by an animal or a tractor.

AGRO:00000223.label: tillage implement
AGRO:00000223.definition: An implement that is used during a tillage process.

AGRO:00000145.label: airblast sprayer
AGRO:00000145.definition:
An implement that uses a combination of air and liquid to deliver liquid material to the target.
It includes include nozzles that deliver spray droplets directly into a high-speed airstream. The air blast shatters the drops of lidquid material into fine droplets and transports them to the target.

AGRO:00000143.label: backpack sprayer
AGRO:00000143.definition: An implement that is used to spray liquid and that is fitted with a harness on the operator back.

AGRO:00000141.label: broadcast spreader
AGRO:00000141.definition: An implement that consists of a hopper, a metering unit, and a distribution device that uses centrifugal force to spread material like seeds, fertilizer granules, liming material, onto the soil surface.

AGRO:00000146.label: furrow opener
AGRO:00000146.definition: An implement which is used to create well-defined grooves in the soil where some material like seeds or fertilizer can be placed at a proper depth.

AGRO:00000144.label: hand sprayer
AGRO:00000144.definition: An implement that is used to spray liquid and is help in the hand. It usually has an air pump which compresses air into the tanks and pressurizes the liquid to spray.

AGRO:00000139.label: manure spreader
AGRO:00000139.definition: An implement used to distribute manure over a field. It usually consists of a trailer towed behind a tractor with a rotating mechanism driven by the tractor's power take off.

AGRO:00000140.label: slurry injector
AGRO:00000140.definition: An implement designed to inject slurry into the soil.

AGRO:00000401.label: dibbling stick
AGRO:00000401.definition: Manually operated device for creating a conical cavity in the soil for sowing of seeds. It consists of a wooden round stick with one end having a sheet metal cone. The other end is provided with a handgrip.

AGRO:00000407.label: double disck opener planter
AGRO:00000407.definition: Double flat and circular piece of metal used to open the soil before putting the seed into the soil.

AGRO:00000405.label: earth auger
AGRO:00000405.definition: Manually operated hand tool that consists of cutter head having semicircular blades connected to pipe with the help of clamp and flange. The connecting pipe is further connected to a handle.

AGRO:00000403.label: hand dibbler
AGRO:00000403.definition: An tool made of mild steel flat or leaf spring by forging operation. The working end is flattened and edge made sharp for easy penetration in the soil.

AGRO:00000402.label: naveen dibbler
AGRO:00000402.definition: Manually operated hand tool which consists of a seed hopper, cell roller for metering of seeds, spring actuated jaws for penetration in the soil, pipe and handle.

AGRO:00000404.label: rotary dibbler
AGRO:00000404.definition: Manually operated push device for dibbling of medium and bold size seeds. It consists of a rotating dibbling head with penetrating jaws, covering-cum-transport wheel, seed hopper with cell wooden roller and a handle.

AGRO:00000406.label: single disc opener planter
AGRO:00000406.definition: A flat and circular piece of metal used to open the soil before putting the seed into the soil.

AGRO:00000232.label: sowing implement
AGRO:00000232.definition: An implement that is used during a sowing process.

AGRO:00000400.label: tyne opener planter
AGRO:00000400.definition: A curved metal bar used to open the soil before putting the seed into the soil.

AGRO:00000142.label: seeding process
AGRO:00000142.definition: A planned process in which seeds are applied on or into the soil.

AGRO:00000397.label: drum seeder
AGRO:00000397.definition: A seeding implement that consists of a seed drum, main shaft, ground wheel, floats, and handle. Joining smaller ends of frustum of cones makes the seed drum.

AGRO:00000398.label: hoe
AGRO:00000398.definition: An agricultural hand tool ade of a blade set to an handle and used to shape the soil, control weeds, clear soil, and harvest root crops.

AGRO:00000396.label: seed drill
AGRO:00000396.definition: A sowing device that positions seeds in the soil and then covers them. The seed drill sows the seeds at equal distances and proper depth, ensuring that the seeds get covered with soil.

AGRO:00000455.label: flail
AGRO:00000455.definition: Agricultural tool made from two or more large sticks attached by a short chain; one stick is held and swung, causing the other to strike a pile of grain, loosening the husks.

AGRO:00000456.label: scythe
AGRO:00000456.definition: Agricultural tool that consists of a shaft about 170 centimetres (67 in) long made of wood or metal. The shaft has either one or two short handles at right angles to it, usually one near the upper end and always another roughly in the middle. A curved, steel blade between 60 to 90 centimetres (24 to 35 in) long is mounted at the lower end at 90°, or less, to the shaft. It is hand powered.

AGRO:00000453.label: sickle
AGRO:00000453.definition: Agricultural tool that is hand-held and composed of a curved blade with a sharp inside and a handle. It is used for harvesting, or reaping, grain crops or cutting succulent forage chiefly for feeding livestock, either freshly cut or dried as hay.

AGRO:00000240.label: animal traction
AGRO:00000240.definition: A traction that uses animal power to pulled an implement.

AGRO:00000238.label: human power
AGRO:00000238.definition: A traction that uses only human power to use an implement.

AGRO:00000239.label: motorized traction
AGRO:00000239.definition: A traction that uses motorized power to pulled an implement.

AGRO:00000198.label: center pivot irrigation machine
AGRO:00000198.definition: Form of overhead sprinkler irrigation consisting of several segments of pipe joined together and supported by trusses, mounted on wheeled towers with sprinklers positioned along its length. The machine moves in a circular pattern and is fed with water from the pivot point at the center of the circle.
AGRO:00000198.synonyms: circle irrigation machine;central pivot irrigation machine

AGRO:00000162.label: irrigation tube
AGRO:00000162.definition: Object with a tube shape used to carry irrigation water through the field

AGRO:00000245.label: material area density recording
AGRO:00000245.definition: Protocol in which the weight or the volume of the material is recorded from the packaging of the material. This value is then divided by the surface area over which the material is applied to obtain the area density of the material.

AGRO:00000244.label: material volume per area measurement protocol
AGRO:00000244.definition: Protocol in which the volume of a material is mesured with a graduated container. The volume of the material is then divided by the surface area over which the material is applied to obtain the area density of the material.

AGRO:00000243.label: material weight per area measurement protocol
AGRO:00000243.definition: Protocol in which the material is weighed with a scale. The weight of the material is then divided by the surface area over which the material is applied to obtain the area density of the material.

AGRO:00000256.label: agricultural process depth measurement protocol using a penometer
AGRO:00000256.definition: Use of a penometer to measure the depth of the agricultural process.

AGRO:00000257.label: implement lenght measurement protocol
AGRO:00000257.definition: Measure the length of the implement that goes into the soil to realize the agricultural process to knoe the depth of the agricultural process. For exemple, measure the length of the tool blade used for tillage to evaluate tillage depth.

AGRO:00000260.label: plant density measurement protocol using quadrat
AGRO:00000260.definition:
Count the number of plants using a quadrat. A quadrat is a frame of a know area. Set the quadrat on the soil and count the number of plants inside it. Repeat this observation as often as mentioned in your sampling protocol.

Total number of plants= [(total number of plants counted inside the quadrat during all the observations)/ (quadrat area)/(number of observation)]x field size.
AGRO:00000260.synonyms: plant population measurement protocol using quadrat

AGRO:00000261.label: plant density simple measurement protocol
AGRO:00000261.definition:
Count the number of plants in a defined area.

Plant density= Total number of plants/ defined area

AGRO:00000268.label: lignin concentration measurement Klason protocol
AGRO:00000268.definition: Measure the lignin concentration with the Klason method.

AGRO:00000265.label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using acetylbromide
AGRO:00000265.definition: Measure the lignin concentration following the acetylbromide method.

AGRO:00000266.label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using acid detergent fiber
AGRO:00000266.definition: Measure the lignin concentration following the acid detergent fiber method

AGRO:00000270.label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using acid detergent lignin
AGRO:00000270.definition: Measure the lignin concentration with the acid detergent lignin method.

AGRO:00000269.label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using permanganate
AGRO:00000269.definition: Measure the lignin concentration with the permanganate method.

AGRO:00000267.label: lignin concentration measurement protocol using thioglycolic acid
AGRO:00000267.definition: Measure the lignin concentration with the thioglycolic acid method.

AGRO:00000273.label: dry combustion method
AGRO:00000273.definition: Protocol used to determine organic carbon content in environmental material according to the amount of CO2 released during combustion of the material.

AGRO:00000272.label: kjeldahl method
AGRO:00000272.definition: Method for the quantitative determination of organic nitrogen in chemical substance.

AGRO:00000271.label: walkley-black method
AGRO:00000271.definition: A determination of organic carbon protocol that uses chromic acid to measure the oxidizable organic carbon in an environmental material.

AGRO:00000276.label: weight loss on ignition method
AGRO:00000276.synonyms: LOI method;Protocol used to measure soil organic matter and soil organic carbon. The method is based upon measuring the weight loss from a dry soil sample when exposed to high temperatures (between 350\xb0C and 600\xb0C). The weight loss that occurs at this temperature is then correlated to oxidizable organic carbon.

AGRO:00000287.label: area direct measurement
AGRO:00000287.definition: Measure the field area in the field.

AGRO:00000288.label: area measurement using cartography
AGRO:00000288.definition: Measure the field area using a map (paper or electronic format).

AGRO:00000289.label: area recording protocol
AGRO:00000289.definition: Record the information giving by a person that knows the field area (farmer, field owner).

AGRO:00000292.label: soil coverage manual measurement protocol
AGRO:00000292.definition: Measure the percentage of soil covered by environmental material by counting the environmental material using quadrat, rope with knots or other devices.

AGRO:00000293.label: soil coverage measurement using GIS
AGRO:00000293.definition: Use GIS to measure the percentage of soil covered by environmental material.

AGRO:00000291.label: soil coverage visual assessment protocol
AGRO:00000291.definition: Assess visually the percentage of soil covered by environmental material.

AGRO:00000298.label: incorporation percentage manual measurement
AGRO:00000298.definition: Measure the percentage of environmental material that has been buried into soil by counting the environmental material using quadrat, rope with knots or other devices befor and after the incorporation process.

AGRO:00000297.label: incorporation percentage measurement using GIS
AGRO:00000297.definition: Use GIS to measure the percentage of environmental material that has been buried into soil during the incorporation process.

AGRO:00000296.label: incorporation percentage visual assessment
AGRO:00000296.definition: Assess visually the percentage of environmental material that has been buried into soil during the incorporation process.

AGRO:00000327.label: number of crops previously cultivated
AGRO:00000327.definition: Number of crops cultivated at the same time during the previous year in the field where the experiment is done.

AGRO:00000337.label: alpha lattice design
AGRO:00000337.definition: A lattice design that is a resolvable incomplete block design where the number of treatments or block size does not meet the strict requirements for one of the lattice designs. Also the number of entries is a multiple of block size.

AGRO:00000336.label: square lattice design
AGRO:00000336.definition: A lattice design in which the number of treatment must be a perfect square. Blocks per replicate and plots per block are equal, and are the square root of the number of treatments.

ENVO:00000083.label: hill
ENVO:00000083.definition: A rounded elevation of limited extent rising above the surrounding land with local relief of less than 300m.

ENVO:00000081.label: mountain
ENVO:00000081.definition: A landform that extends above the surrounding terrain in a limited area. A mountain is generally steeper than a hill, but there is no universally accepted standard definition for the height of a mountain or a hill although a mountain usually has an identifiable summit and a local relief of more than 300m.

ENVO:00000086.label: plain
ENVO:00000086.definition: A region of general uniform slope, comparatively level, and of considerable extent.

ENVO:00000182.label: plateau
ENVO:00000182.definition: An elevated and comparatively level expanse of land.

ENVO:00000100.label: valley
ENVO:00000100.definition: A depression which has been formed as a result of erosion by water or ice and which is low-lying, bordered by higher ground, and especially elongate.

ENVO:00000091.label: beach
ENVO:00000091.definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a body of water.

ENVO:00000150.label: coral reef
ENVO:00000150.definition: Aragonite structures produced by living organisms, found in shallow, marine waters with little nutrients in the water.

ENVO:00000309.label: depression
ENVO:00000309.definition: A landform sunken or depressed below the surrounding area.

ENVO:00000170.label: dune
ENVO:00000170.definition: A hill of sand built by eolian processes.

ENVO:00000527.label: interfluve
ENVO:00000527.definition: A relatively undissected upland between adjacent stream valleys.

ENVO:00000038.label: lagoon
ENVO:00000038.definition: A sheet of saline water separated from the open sea by sand or shingle banks. The sheet of water between an offshore reef, especially of coral and mainland. The sheet of water within a ring or horseshoe shaped atoll.

ENVO:00000057.label: mangrove swamp
ENVO:00000057.definition: An swamp formed of trees and shrubs that grow in saline coastal habitats in the tropics and subtropics.

ENVO:00000283.label: ridge
ENVO:00000283.definition: A long and narrow upland with steep sides.

ENVO:00002000.label: slope
ENVO:00002000.definition: The part of an elevation or depression between the relatively flat surrounding area and the peak of a mount or the bottom of a depression.

AGRO:00000332.label: completely randomized design
AGRO:00000332.definition: An experimental design in which the treatments are assigned completely at random so that each experimental unit has the same chance of receiving any one treatment. Any difference among experimental units receiving the same treatment is considered as experimental error. Hence, it is appropriate only for experiments with homogeneous experimental units, such as laboratory experiments, where environmental effects are relatively easy to control.

AGRO:00000335.label: demonstration strip design
AGRO:00000335.definition: An experimental design in which basic farming practices are compared using demonstration strips on a farm field. Usually the comparison is between two to four treatments, up to a maximum of 10 and each treatment is included only once.

AGRO:00000331.label: factorial design
AGRO:00000331.definition: An experimental design in which two or more factors, each with discrete possible values or "levels", and whose experimental units take on all possible combinations of these levels across all such factors. That is, the design provides information on the average effect of the individual factors as well as the interaction between these two factors.

AGRO:00000333.label: lattice design
AGRO:00000333.definition: An experimental design in which the blocks should be composed of plots that are as homogeneous as possible. Further, blocks in the same replication should be as near as possible to maximize the variation among replication. These incomplete blocks are combined into groups that form separate, complete replications.

OBI:0500007.label: randomized complete block design
OBI:0500007.definition: A randomized complete block design is_a study design which assigns randomly treatments to block. The number of units per block equals the number of treatment so each block receives each treatment exactly once (hence the qualifier 'complete'). The design was originally devised from field trials used in agronomy and agriculture. The analysis assumes that there is no interaction between block and treatment. The method was then used in other settings So The randomised complete block design is a design in which the subjects are matched according to a variable which the experimenter wishes to control. The subjects are put into groups (blocks) of the same size as the number of treatments. The members of each block are then randomly assigned to different treatment groups.

AGRO:00000334.label: replicated control design
AGRO:00000334.definition: An experimental design in which each treatment is included only once and is near to a control treatment. A control treatment is usually either a common practice or no practice.

AGRO:00000329.label: split plot design
AGRO:00000329.definition: An experimental design that enables an additional factor or treatment to be included at more than one level; each plot is split into two or more parts.

AGRO:00000330.label: strip plot design
AGRO:00000330.definition:
An experimental design in which the desired precision for measuring the interaction effect between the two factors is higher than that for measuring the main effect of either one of  the two factors. This is accomplished with the use of three plot sizes : 
1. Vertical strip plot for the first factor – vertical factor 
2. Horizontal strip plot for the second factor – horizontal factor 
3. Interaction plot for the interaction between 2 factors

ENVO:1000745.label: drought
ENVO:1000745.definition: A hydrological precipitation process with a reduced rate relative to some historical average, typically resulting in ecosystemic perturbations.

AGRO:00000345.label: equipement complication
AGRO:00000345.definition: A complication with the equipement used during the experiment.

ENVO:01000710.label: flood
ENVO:01000710.definition: An unusual accumulation of water above the ground caused by high tide, heavy rain, melting snow or rapid runoff from paved areas.

AGRO:00000346.label: personel complication
AGRO:00000346.definition: A complication with a person or a group of people working on the experiement.

ENVO:01000787.label: wildfire
ENVO:01000787.definition: A conflagration which is uncontrolled and combusts material in a vegetated area, be it rural or wild.

AGRO:00000351.label: hill distribution
AGRO:00000351.definition: Planting is done on flat-top circular mounds.

AGRO:00000353.label: row on bed distribution
AGRO:00000353.definition: Planting distribution where the crop zone and the traffic lanes (wheel tracks or furrows) are distinctly and permanently separated. Soil is moved from the traffic lanes and added to the crop zone, slightly raising the surface level of the crop zone

AGRO:00000354.label: uniform distribution
AGRO:00000354.definition: Planting is done on all the field surface.

PATO:0001857.label: concave
PATO:0001857.definition: A shape quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's curving inward.

PATO:0001355.label: convex
PATO:0001355.definition: A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer having inward facing edges; having a surface or boundary that curves or bulges outward, as the exterior of a sphere.

PATO:0002180.label: straight
PATO:0002180.definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being free of curves, bends, or angles.

AGRO:00000388.label: terraced
AGRO:00000388.definition: Slope on which terraces have been build.

AGRO:00000361.label: farmer field
AGRO:00000361.definition: Experimental site in which the experiment is implemented on the field of a farmer.

AGRO:00000364.label: governmental forest
AGRO:00000364.definition: Experimental site where the experiment is done in a forest owned by a government.

AGRO:00000363.label: greenhouse
AGRO:00000363.definition: An experimental site in which the experiment is performed in a structure with walls and roof made chiefly of transparent material, such as glass, with the possibility to regulate climatic conditions.

AGRO:00000365.label: private forest
AGRO:00000365.definition: Experimental site where the experiment is done in a private forest.

AGRO:00000362.label: research station field
AGRO:00000362.definition: Experimental site in which the experiment is done in a the field of a research station.

AGRO:00000370.label: agricultural experiment
AGRO:00000370.definition: An experiment in which a scientific method is implemented for testing certain agricultural phenomena.

AGRO:00000379.label: data collector
AGRO:00000379.definition: A person that has a role of collecting data related to the experiment.

AGRO:00000381.label: experiment manager
AGRO:00000381.definition: A person that has a role of managing the experiment.

AGRO:00000376.label: extension agent
AGRO:00000376.definition: A person that is employed by the government to assist people in rural areas with methods of farming and home economics.

AGRO:00000377.label: faculty member
AGRO:00000377.definition: A person that is an educator who works at a college or university.

AGRO:00000372.label: farmer
AGRO:00000372.definition: A person engaged in agriculture, raising living organisms for food or raw materials.

AGRO:00000382.label: field laborer
AGRO:00000382.definition: A person that has a role of performing the operations required to run the experiment in the field.

AGRO:00000380.label: principal investigator
AGRO:00000380.definition: A person that is the holder of an independent grant and the lead researcher for the grant project.

AGRO:00000375.label: research station employee
AGRO:00000375.definition: A person that works in a research station.

AGRO:00000374.label: student
AGRO:00000374.definition: A person that is enrolled or attends classes at a school, college, or university.

AGRO:00000385.label: flower strip
AGRO:00000385.definition: Strip of flowers established at the edge of the field.

ENVO:00000114.label: agricultural field
ENVO:00000114.definition: An area of land, usually relatively small, enclosed or otherwise and used for agricultural purposes.

ENVO:01001305.label: vegetated area
ENVO:01001305.definition: A vegetated area is a geographic feature which has ground cover dominated by plant communities.

AGRO:00000399.label: manual oilseed drill
AGRO:00000399.definition:
A seed drill that consists of a seed box attached to the mainframe of a hand wheel hoe. A fluted roller assembly is provided at the bottom of the seed box. Fluted roller is rotated with the help of
chain and sprockets from the ground wheel.

AGRO:00000227.label: fertilization implement
AGRO:00000227.definition: An implement that is used during a fertilization process.

AGRO:00000234.label: harvest implement
AGRO:00000234.definition: An implement that is used in an harvest process.

AGRO:00000241.label: irrigation equipment
AGRO:00000241.definition: An equipment that is used during an irrigation process.

AGRO:00000224.label: land levelling implement
AGRO:00000224.definition: An implement that is used during a land levelling process.

AGRO:00000236.label: mulch implement
AGRO:00000236.definition: An implement that is used during a mulch process.

AGRO:00000230.label: planting implement
AGRO:00000230.definition: An implement that is used in a planting process.

AGRO:00000225.label: residue management implement
AGRO:00000225.definition: An implement that is used during a residue management process.

AGRO:00000124.label: tractor
AGRO:00000124.definition: A mobile machine specifically designed to deliver a high tractive effort at slow speeds, and mainly used for the purposes of hauling a trailer or machinery used in agriculture or construction.

AGRO:00000228.label: transplanting implement
AGRO:00000228.definition: An implement that is used during a transplanting process.

AGRO:00000431.label: continuous grazing
AGRO:00000431.definition: A grazing management system in which livestock have unrestricted access to the pasture area throughout the grazing season.

AGRO:00000430.label: rotational grazing
AGRO:00000430.definition: A grazing management system in which the land is subdivided or sectioned off into smaller areas, sometimes called paddocks. The livestock are moved from one paddock to another in order to best promote plant health and growth.

AGRO:00000436.label: creep grazing
AGRO:00000436.definition: A grazzing management system that allows young farm animals to graze part of the pasture before the adults. It employs a gate through which young animals, but not adults, can pass to get first choice of fresh feed in the next door paddock.

AGRO:00000437.label: first-last grazing
AGRO:00000437.definition: A gazing management system in which two or more groups of animal, usually with different nutritional needs, graze the same paddock but at different time.

AGRO:00000433.label: intensive rotational grazing
AGRO:00000433.definition: A rotational grazing management system that implies many paddocks are utilized and livestock are moved on a frequent basis. It provides more stable production during poor growing conditions, greater yield, higher quality, decreased weed and erosion, and uniform soil fertility levels.

AGRO:00000434.label: controlled grazing
AGRO:00000434.definition: An intensive rotational grazing system in which livestock is allowed to graze for a limited time, leaving a leafy stubble, and then is moved to another area.

AGRO:00000435.label: hohenheim grazing system
AGRO:00000435.definition: Intensive grazing system in which the field is divided into many small plots of equal size. Grasses are raised with application of large quantities of nitrogenous fertilizers. The livestock are divided into three groups : high, medium and low yeilders. They are let into the paddock by rotation so that the opportunity for grazing most nutritious immature grasses goes to the high yielders followed by medium producers and lastly low yielders.

AGRO:00000427.label: holistic planned grazing
AGRO:00000427.definition: Grazing management system developped by Allan Savory. The system is based on a rotational grazing system but doing so at high densities for short intervals. Livestock is used as a tool to increase soil fertility and plant life. Incorporating plant organic matter and manure into the soil promotes the recycling of nutrients.

AGRO:00000428.label: mob grazing
AGRO:00000428.definition: A grazing management method that involves moving livestock at least daily between small paddocks, sized to match the number of grazing animals, and split by fence. The goal is for every plant in the grazing cell to be either eaten or walked on and trampled. Grass in each paddock then rests for 60-120 days or more.

AGRO:00000432.label: strip grazing
AGRO:00000432.definition: A system of grazing which confined animals to a strip or small part of the field for rapid grazing in a short time period.. The rest of the field is protected by a temporary fence, usually electric.

AGRO:00000026.label: no-till
AGRO:00000026.definition: A planned process in which the soil is left undisturbed apart from where the seeds or planting material are placed.

BFO:0000002.label: continuant
BFO:0000002.definition: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

BFO:0000003.label: occurrent
BFO:0000003.definition: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

BFO:0000031.label: generically dependent continuant
BFO:0000031.definition: b is a generically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant that g-depends_on one or more other entities. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001])

BFO:0000004.label: independent continuant
BFO:0000004.definition: b is an independent continuant = Def. b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends_on c at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002])

BFO:0000020.label: specifically dependent continuant
BFO:0000020.definition: b is a specifically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant & there is some independent continuant c which is not a spatial region and which is such that b s-depends_on c at every time t during the course of b’s existence. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [050-003])

BFO:0000015.label: process
BFO:0000015.definition: p is a process = Def. p is an occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [083-003])

UBERON:0001062.label: anatomical entity
UBERON:0001062.definition: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

BFO:0000040.label: material entity
BFO:0000040.definition: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

GO:0008150.label: biological_process
GO:0008150.definition: Any process specifically pertinent to the functioning of integrated living units: cells, tissues, organs, and organisms. A process is a collection of molecular events with a defined beginning and end.

RO:0002310.label: exposure event or process
RO:0002310.definition: A process occurring within or in the vicinity of an organism that exerts some causal influence on the organism via the interaction between an exposure stimulus and an exposure receptor. The exposure stimulus may be a process, material entity or condition (for example, lack of nutrients). The exposure receptor can be an organism, organism population or a part of an organism.

ENVO:02500000.label: environmental system process
ENVO:02500000.definition: A process in which includes the components of an environmental system as participants.

OBI:0000011.label: planned process
OBI:0000011.definition: A processual entity that realizes a plan which is the concretization of a plan specification.

OBI:0000339.label: planning
OBI:0000339.definition: a process of creating or modifying a plan specification

OGMS:0000031.label: disease
OGMS:0000031.definition: A disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

BFO:0000023.label: role
BFO:0000023.definition: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.

PATO:0000125.label: mass
PATO:0000125.definition: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the proportion of the bearer's amount of matter.

PATO:0000051.label: morphology
PATO:0000051.definition: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

IAO:0000015.label: information carrier
IAO:0000015.definition: A quality of an information bearer that imparts the information content

PATO:0001237.label: quality of a single physical entity
PATO:0001237.definition: A physical object quality which inheres in a single-bearer.

PATO:0000001.label: quality
PATO:0000001.definition: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

BFO:0000017.label: realizable entity
BFO:0000017.definition: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

OBI:0000202.label: investigation agent role
OBI:0000202.definition: A role borne by an entity and that is realized in a process that is part of an investigation in which an objective is achieved. These processes include, among others: planning, overseeing, funding, reviewing.

OBI:0000571.label: manufacturer role
OBI:0000571.definition: Manufacturer role is a role which inheres in a person or organization and which is realized by a manufacturing process.

OBI:0000947.label: service provider role
OBI:0000947.definition: is a role which inheres in a person or organization and is realized in in a planned process which provides access to training, materials or execution of protocols for an organization or person

AGRO:00000069.label: biological pest control agent role
AGRO:00000069.definition: A role that inheres in an organism that is realised in a pest control process where that organism is used to suppress unwanted organisms.

OBI:0000067.label: evaluant role
OBI:0000067.definition: a role that inheres in a material entity that is realized in an assay in which data is generated about the bearer of the evaluant role

AGRO:00000008.label: irrigation water source role
AGRO:00000008.definition: A role that inheres in a water body that is realised in an irrigation process where water is transported from that water body to the target of the irrigation process.

AGRO:00000070.label: liming role
AGRO:00000070.definition: A role that inheres in an environmental material that is realised in a land preparation process where that environmental material is applied to soil in order to neutralize soil acidity.

OBI:0000319.label: material to be added role
OBI:0000319.definition: material to be added role is a protocol participant role realized by a material which is added into a material bearing the target of material addition role in a material addition process

AGRO:00000378.label: person role within the experiment
AGRO:00000378.definition: Roled performed by a person during an experiment.

AGRO:00000035.label: pest role
AGRO:00000035.definition: A role that inheres in an organism that is realized in an agricultural process where the organism is unwanted.

OBI:0000017.label: regulatory role
OBI:0000017.definition: a role which inheres in material entities and is realized in the processes of making, enforcing or being defined by legislation or orders issued by a governmental body.

OBI:0000112.label: specimen role
OBI:0000112.definition: a role borne by a material entity that is gained during a specimen collection process and that can be realized by use of the specimen in an investigation

OBI:0000444.label: target of material addition role
OBI:0000444.definition: target of material addition role is a role realized by an entity into which a material is added in a material addition process

ENVO:01000665.label: waste role
ENVO:01000665.definition: A role that is realized in some process wherein the bearer is discarded or not utilized further.

AGRO:00000357.label: weather station
AGRO:00000357.definition: An observation post where weather conditions and meteorological data are observed and recorded and reported.

IAO:0000030.label: information content entity
IAO:0000030.definition: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

CHEBI:24431.label: chemical entity
CHEBI:24431.definition: A chemical entity is a physical entity of interest in chemistry including molecular entities, parts thereof, and chemical substances.

ENVO:00002297.label: environmental feature
ENVO:00002297.definition: A material entity which determines an environmental system.

ENVO:00010483.label: environmental material
ENVO:00010483.definition: A portion of environmental material is a fiat object which forms the medium or part of the medium of an environmental system.

OBI:0000835.label: manufacturer
OBI:0000835.definition: A person or organization that has a manufacturer role

OBI:1110108.label: material to be added
OBI:1110108.definition: a material that is added to another one in a material combination process

PO:0025131.label: plant anatomical entity
PO:0025131.definition: An anatomical entity that is or was part of a plant.

CHEBI:36342.label: subatomic particle
CHEBI:36342.definition: A particle smaller than an atom.

RO:0002577.label: system
RO:0002577.definition: A material entity consisting of multiple components that are causally integrated.

OBI:1110109.label: target of material addition
OBI:1110109.definition: A material entity into which another is being added in a material combinatino process

OBI:0002076.label: collection of specimens
OBI:0002076.definition: A material entity that has two or more specimens as its parts.

IAO:0000178.label: material information bearer
IAO:0000178.definition: A material entity in which a concretization of an information content entity inheres.

ENVO:01001008.label: meteor
ENVO:01001008.definition: A meteor is any matter- or energy-based entity which is located in the atmosphere of an astronomical body.

OBI:0100026.label: organism
OBI:0100026.definition: A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs.

OBI:0000245.label: organization
OBI:0000245.definition: An entity that can bear roles, has members, and has a set of organization rules. Members of organizations are either organizations themselves or individual people. Members can bear specific organization member roles that are determined in the organization rules. The organization rules also determine how decisions are made on behalf of the organization by the organization members.

OBI:0000047.label: processed material
OBI:0000047.definition: Is a material entity that is created or changed during material processing.

OBI:0100051.label: specimen
OBI:0100051.definition: A material entity that has the specimen role.

CHEBI:16134.label: ammonia
CHEBI:16134.definition: An azane that consists of a single nitrogen atom covelently bonded to three hydrogen atoms.

CHEBI:17997.label: dinitrogen
CHEBI:17997.definition: An elemental molecule consisting of two trivalently-bonded nitrogen atoms.

CHEBI:17883.label: hydrogen chloride
CHEBI:17883.definition: A mononuclear parent hydride consisting of covalently bonded hydrogen and chlorine atoms.

CHEBI:16136.label: hydrogen sulfide
CHEBI:16136.definition: A sulfur hydride consisting of a single sulfur atom bonded to two hydrogen atoms. A highly poisonous, flammable gas with a characteristic odour of rotten eggs, it is often produced by bacterial decomposition of organic matter in the absence of oxygen.

CHEBI:32285.label: ((13)C)urea
CHEBI:32285.definition: A (13)C-modified compound that is urea in which the carbon is present as its (13)C isotope.

CHEBI:139357.label: (13)C-modified compound
CHEBI:139357.definition: An isotopically modified compound in which the abundance of a (13)C isotope at one or more positions has been increased above that of the naturally occurring level.

CHEBI:39142.label: Bronsted base
CHEBI:39142.definition: A molecular entity capable of accepting a hydron from a donor (Bronsted acid).

CHEBI:17996.label: chloride
CHEBI:17996.definition: A halide anion formed when chlorine picks up an electron to form an an anion.

CHEBI:39141.label: Bronsted acid
CHEBI:39141.definition: A molecular entity capable of donating a hydron to an acceptor (Bronsted base).

CHEBI:39144.label: Lewis base
CHEBI:39144.definition: A molecular entity able to provide a pair of electrons and thus capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron-pair acceptor (Lewis acid), thereby producing a Lewis adduct.

CHEBI:37838.label: carboacyl group
CHEBI:37838.definition: A carboacyl group is a group formed by loss of at least one OH from the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid.

CHEBI:25696.label: organic anion
CHEBI:25696.definition: Any organic ion with a net negative charge.

CHEBI:33273.label: polyatomic anion
CHEBI:33273.definition: An anion consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:33259.label: elemental molecular entity
CHEBI:33259.definition: A molecular entity all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

CHEBI:24835.label: inorganic molecular entity
CHEBI:24835.definition: A molecular entity that contains no carbon.

CHEBI:24870.label: ion
CHEBI:24870.definition: A molecular entity having a net electric charge.

CHEBI:139358.label: isotopically modified compound
CHEBI:139358.definition: Any molecular entity in which the isotopic ratio of nuclides for at least one element deviates measurably from that occurring in nature. The term includes both isotopically substituted compounds (in which essentially all the molecules of the compound have only the indicated nuclide(s) at each designated position) and isotopically labeled compounds (a formal mixture of an isotopically unmodified compound with one or more analogous isotopically substituted compound(s).

CHEBI:33579.label: main group molecular entity
CHEBI:33579.definition: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.

CHEBI:36357.label: polyatomic entity
CHEBI:36357.definition: Any molecular entity consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:74783.label: astringent
CHEBI:74783.definition: A compound that causes the contraction of body tissues, typically used to reduce bleeding from minor abrasions.

CHEBI:35554.label: cardiovascular drug
CHEBI:35554.definition: A drug that affects the rate or intensity of cardiac contraction, blood vessel diameter or blood volume.

CHEBI:76759.label: EC 3.* (hydrolase) inhibitor
CHEBI:76759.definition: Any enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase (EC 3.*.*.*).

CHEBI:33250.label: atom
CHEBI:33250.definition: A chemical entity constituting the smallest component of an element having the chemical properties of the element.

CHEBI:59999.label: chemical substance
CHEBI:59999.definition: A chemical substance is a portion of matter of constant composition, composed of molecular entities of the same type or of different types.

CHEBI:24433.label: group
CHEBI:24433.definition: A defined linked collection of atoms or a single atom within a molecular entity.

CHEBI:23367.label: molecular entity
CHEBI:23367.definition: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

CHEBI:52209.label: aetiopathogenetic role
CHEBI:52209.definition: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof which causes the development of a pathological process.

CHEBI:52206.label: biochemical role
CHEBI:52206.definition: A biological role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biochemical context.

CHEBI:35222.label: inhibitor
CHEBI:35222.definition: A substance that diminishes the rate of a chemical reaction.

CHEBI:64909.label: poison
CHEBI:64909.definition: Any substance that causes disturbance to organisms by chemical reaction or other activity on the molecular scale, when a sufficient quantity is absorbed by the organism.

CHEBI:33246.label: inorganic group
CHEBI:33246.definition: Any substituent group which does not contain carbon.

CHEBI:33247.label: organic group
CHEBI:33247.definition: Any substituent group or skeleton containing carbon.

CHEBI:23117.label: chlorine molecular entity
CHEBI:23117.definition: A halogen molecular entity containing one or more atoms of chlorine.

CHEBI:37578.label: halide
CHEBI:37578.definition: Any heteroatomic molecular entity that is a chemical compound of halogen with other chemical elements.

CHEBI:24833.label: oxoacid
CHEBI:24833.definition: A compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

CHEBI:79388.label: divalent inorganic anion
CHEBI:79388.definition: Any inorganic anion with a valency of two.

CHEBI:79389.label: monovalent inorganic anion
CHEBI:79389.definition: Any inorganic anion with a valency of one.

CHEBI:79387.label: trivalent inorganic anion
CHEBI:79387.definition: Any inorganic anion with a valency of three.

CHEBI:63038.label: ammonium nitrate
CHEBI:63038.definition: The ammonium salt of nitric acid.

CHEBI:24838.label: inorganic phosphate
CHEBI:24838.definition: Any  phosphate that contains no carbon atom.

CHEBI:63051.label: diammonium hydrogen phosphate
CHEBI:63051.definition: An inorganic phosphate, being the diammonium salt of phosphoric acid.
CHEBI:63051.synonyms: Diammonium hydrogen phosphate;diazanium hydrogen phosphate;diammonium hydrogen phosphate

CHEBI:62946.label: ammonium sulfate
CHEBI:62946.definition: An inorganic sulfate salt obtained by reaction of sulfuric acid with two equivalents of ammonia. A high-melting (decomposes above 280degreeC) white solid which is very soluble in water (70.6 g/100 g water at 0degreeC; 103.8 g/100 g water at 100degreeC), it is widely used as a fertilizer for alkaline soils.

CHEBI:22563.label: anion
CHEBI:22563.definition: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the electron.

CHEBI:36916.label: cation
CHEBI:36916.definition: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the proton.

CHEBI:36358.label: polyatomic ion
CHEBI:36358.definition: An ion consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:75763.label: eukaryotic metabolite
CHEBI:75763.definition: Any  metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in eukaryotes, the taxon that include members of the fungi, plantae and animalia kingdoms.

CHEBI:75787.label: prokaryotic metabolite
CHEBI:75787.definition: Any metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in prokaryotes, the taxon that include members of domains such as the bacteria and archaea.

CHEBI:27026.label: toxin
CHEBI:27026.definition: Poisonous substance produced by a biological organism such as a microbe, animal or plant.

CHEBI:60240.label: divalent metal cation
CHEBI:60240.definition: A metal cation with a valence of two.

CHEBI:33595.label: cyclic compound
CHEBI:33595.definition: Any molecule that consists of a series of atoms joined together to form a ring.

CHEBI:25362.label: elemental molecule
CHEBI:25362.definition: A molecule all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

CHEBI:72695.label: organic molecule
CHEBI:72695.definition: Any molecule that consists of at least one carbon atom as part of the electrically neutral entity.

CHEBI:29103.label: potassium(1+)
CHEBI:29103.definition: A monoatomic monocation obtained from potassium.

CHEBI:35604.label: carbon oxoanion
CHEBI:35604.definition: A negative ion consisting solely of carbon and oxygen  atoms, and therefore having the general formula CxOy(n-) for some integers x, y and n.

CHEBI:29067.label: carboxylic acid anion
CHEBI:29067.definition: The conjugate base formed when the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid is deprotonated.

CHEBI:35406.label: oxoanion
CHEBI:35406.definition: An oxoanion is an anion derived from an oxoacid by loss of hydron(s) bound to oxygen.

CHEBI:24651.label: hydroxides
CHEBI:24651.definition: Hydroxides are chemical compounds containing a hydroxy group or salts containing hydroxide (OH(-)).

CHEBI:36963.label: organooxygen compound
CHEBI:36963.definition: An organochalcogen compound containing at least one carbon-oxygen bond.

CHEBI:25741.label: oxide
CHEBI:25741.definition: An oxide is a chemical compound of oxygen with other chemical elements.

CHEBI:26020.label: phosphate
CHEBI:26020.definition: Salts and esters of phosphoric and oligophosphoric acids and their chalcogen analogues. In inorganic chemistry, the term is also used to describe anionic coordination entities with phosphorus as central atom.

CHEBI:6457.label: lignin
CHEBI:6457.definition: A polyphenylpropanoid derived from three monolignol monomers: trans-p-coumaryl alcohol, coniferol and trans-sinapyl alcohol. There is extensive cross-linking and no defined primary structure.

CHEBI:26218.label: potassium salt
CHEBI:26218.definition: Any alkali metal salt having potassium(1+) as the cation.

CHEBI:32588.label: potassium chloride
CHEBI:32588.definition: A metal chloride salt with a K(+) counterion.

CHEBI:63043.label: potassium nitrate
CHEBI:63043.definition: The inorganic nitrate salt of potassium.

CHEBI:23004.label: carbamoyl group
CHEBI:23004.definition: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of carbamic acid.

CHEBI:16199.label: urea
CHEBI:16199.definition: A carbonyl group with two C-bound amine groups.

CHEBI:33256.label: primary amide
CHEBI:33256.definition: A derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

CHEBI:33286.label: agrochemical
CHEBI:33286.definition: An agrochemical is a substance that is used in agriculture or horticulture.

CHEBI:64047.label: food additive
CHEBI:64047.definition: Any substance which is added to food to preserve or enhance its flavour and/or appearance.

CHEBI:25944.label: pesticide
CHEBI:25944.definition: Strictly, a substance intended to kill pests. In common usage, any substance used for controlling, preventing, or destroying animal, microbiological or plant pests.

CHEBI:52217.label: pharmaceutical
CHEBI:52217.definition: Any substance introduced into a living organism with therapeutic or diagnostic purpose.

CHEBI:76414.label: propellant
CHEBI:76414.definition: A compressed gas or liquid with a boiling point lower than room temperature which to used to propel and dispense liquids such as deodorants, insecticides, paints, etc. from aerosol cans.

CHEBI:33893.label: reagent
CHEBI:33893.definition: A substance used in a chemical reaction to detect, measure, examine, or produce other substances.

CHEBI:78433.label: refrigerant
CHEBI:78433.definition: A substance used in a thermodynamic heat pump cycle or refrigeration cycle that undergoes a phase change from a gas to a liquid and back. Refrigerants are used in air-conditioning systems and freezers or refrigerators and are assigned a "R" number (by ASHRAE - formerly the American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers), which is determined systematically according to their molecular structure.

CHEBI:46787.label: solvent
CHEBI:46787.definition: A liquid that can dissolve other substances (solutes) without any change in their chemical composition.

CHEBI:36338.label: lepton
CHEBI:36338.definition: Lepton is a fermion that does not experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek lambdaepsilonpitauomicronsigma (small, thin).

CHEBI:48377.label: imidic acid
CHEBI:48377.definition: Compounds derived from oxoacids RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) by replacing =O by =NR; thus tautomers of amides. In organic chemistry an unspecified imidic acid is generally a carboximidic acid, RC(=NR)(OH).

CHEBI:22221.label: acyl group
CHEBI:22221.definition: An organic group formed by removing one or more hydroxy groups from an oxoacid that has the general structure RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0). Although the term is almost always applied to organic compounds, with carboxylic acid as the oxoacid, acyl groups can in principle be derived from other types of acids such as sulfonic acids or phosphonic acids.

CHEBI:33318.label: main group element atom
CHEBI:33318.definition: An atom belonging to one of the main groups (found in the s- and p- blocks) of the periodic table.

CHEBI:33521.label: metal atom
CHEBI:33521.definition: An atom of an element that exhibits typical metallic properties, being typically shiny, with high electrical and thermal conductivity.

CHEBI:137980.label: metalloid atom
