CHEBI:137980.definition: An atom of an element that exhibits properties that are between those of metals and nonmetals, or that has a mixture of them. The term generally includes boron, silicon, germanium, arsenic, antimony, and tellurium, while carbon, aluminium, selenium, polonium, and astatine are less commonly included.

CHEBI:37622.label: carboxamide
CHEBI:37622.definition: An amide of a carboxylic acid, having the structure RC(=O)NR2. The term is used as a suffix in systematic name formation to denote the -C(=O)NH2 group including its carbon atom.

CHEBI:33238.label: monoatomic entity
CHEBI:33238.definition: A monoatomic entity is a molecular entity consisting of a single atom.

CHEBI:62488.label: signalling molecule
CHEBI:62488.definition: A molecular messenger in which the molecule is specifically involved in transmitting information between cells. Such molecules are released from the cell sending the signal, cross over the gap between cells by diffusion, and interact with specific receptors in another cell, triggering a response in that cell by activating a series of enzyme controlled reactions which lead to changes inside the cell.

CHEBI:27027.label: micronutrient
CHEBI:27027.definition: Any nutrient required in small quantities by organisms throughout their life in order to orchestrate a range of physiological functions.

CHEBI:36962.label: organochalcogen compound
CHEBI:36962.definition: An organochalcogen compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-chalcogen bond.

CHEBI:35352.label: organonitrogen compound
CHEBI:35352.definition: Any heteroorganic entity containing at least one carbon-nitrogen bond.

CHEBI:33287.label: fertilizer
CHEBI:33287.definition: A fertilizer is any substance that is added to soil or water to assist the growth of plants.

AGRO:00000034.label: inorganic fertilizer
AGRO:00000034.definition: A fertilizer that does not contain a carbon-hydrogen linkage.

AGRO:00000033.label: organic fertilizer
AGRO:00000033.definition: A fertilizer that is derived from animal or vegetable matter, and contains a carbon-hydrogen linkage.

CHEBI:33560.label: p-block element atom
CHEBI:33560.definition: Any main group element atom belonging to the p-block of the periodic table.

CHEBI:18248.label: iron atom
CHEBI:18248.definition: An iron group element atom that has atomic number 26.

CHEBI:26836.label: sulfuric acid
CHEBI:26836.definition: A sulfur oxoacid that consits of two oxo and two hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central sulfur atom.
CHEBI:26836.synonyms: Sulfuric acid;dihydroxidodioxidosulfur;dihydrogen tetraoxosulfate;hydrogen tetraoxosulfate(VI);sulfuric acid;tetraoxosulfuric acid;hydrogen tetraoxosulfate(2-)

CHEBI:33457.label: phosphorus oxoacid
CHEBI:33457.definition: A pnictogen oxoacid which contains phosphorus and oxygen, at least one hydrogen atom bound to oxygen, and forms an ion by the loss of one or more protons.

CHEBI:16042.label: halide anion
CHEBI:16042.definition: A monoatomic monoanion resulting from the addition of an electron to any halogen atom.

CHEBI:48107.label: nitric acid
CHEBI:48107.definition: A nitrogen oxoacid of formula HNO3 in which the nitrogen atom is bonded to a hydroxy group and by equivalent bonds to the remaining two oxygen atoms.

CHEBI:59698.label: phosphoric acids
CHEBI:59698.definition: Compounds containing one or more phosphoric acid units.

CHEBI:17632.label: nitrate
CHEBI:17632.definition: A nitrogen oxoanion formed by loss of a proton from nitric acid. Principal species present at pH 7.3.

CHEBI:35780.label: phosphate ion
CHEBI:35780.definition: A phosphorus oxoanion that is the conjugate base of phosphoric acid.

CHEBI:16189.label: sulfate
CHEBI:16189.definition: A sulfur oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of both OH groups of sulfuric acid.

CHEBI:27081.label: transition element atom
CHEBI:27081.definition: An element whose atom has an incomplete d sub-shell, or which can give rise to cations with an incomplete d sub-shell.

CHEBI:33303.label: chalcogen
CHEBI:33303.definition: Any p-block element belonging to the group 16 family of the periodic table.

CHEBI:33300.label: pnictogen
CHEBI:33300.definition: Any p-block element atom that is in group 15 of the periodic table: nitrogen, phosphorus, arsenic, antimony and bismuth.

CHEBI:33709.label: amino acid
CHEBI:33709.definition: A carboxylic acid containing one or more amino groups.

CHEBI:138675.label: gas molecular entity
CHEBI:138675.definition: Any main group molecular entity that is gaseous at standard temperature and pressure (STP; 0degreeC and 100 kPa).

CHEBI:33675.label: p-block molecular entity
CHEBI:33675.definition: A main group molecular entity that contains one or more atoms of a p-block element.

CHEBI:33674.label: s-block molecular entity
CHEBI:33674.definition: An s-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an s-block element.

CHEBI:50860.label: organic molecular entity
CHEBI:50860.definition: Any molecular entity that contains carbon.

CHEBI:33655.label: aromatic compound
CHEBI:33655.definition: A cyclically conjugated molecular entity with a stability (due to delocalization) significantly greater than that of a hypothetical localized structure (e.g. Kekule structure) is said to possess aromatic character.

CHEBI:33832.label: organic cyclic compound
CHEBI:33832.definition: Any organic molecule that consists of atoms connected in the form of a ring.

CHEBI:33405.label: hydracid
CHEBI:33405.definition: A hydracid is a compound which contains hydrogen that is not bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

CHEBI:33692.label: hydrides
CHEBI:33692.definition: Hydrides are chemical compounds of hydrogen with other chemical elements.

CHEBI:26004.label: phenylpropanoid
CHEBI:26004.definition: Any organic aromatic compound with a structure based on a phenylpropane skeleton. The class includes naturally occurring phenylpropanoid esters, flavonoids, anthocyanins, coumarins and many small phenolic molecules as well as their semi-synthetic and synthetic analogues. Phenylpropanoids are also precursors of lignin.

CHEBI:33296.label: alkali metal molecular entity
CHEBI:33296.definition: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an alkali metal.

CHEBI:33299.label: alkaline earth molecular entity
CHEBI:33299.definition: An alkaline earth molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an alkaline earth metal.

CHEBI:33304.label: chalcogen molecular entity
CHEBI:33304.definition: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.

CHEBI:33302.label: pnictogen molecular entity
CHEBI:33302.definition: A p-block molecular entity containing any pnictogen.

CHEBI:15377.label: water
CHEBI:15377.definition: An oxygen hydride consisting of an oxygen atom that is covalently bonded to two hydrogen atoms.

CHEBI:35274.label: ammonium ion
CHEBI:35274.definition: Ammonium, NH4(+), and derivatives formed by substitution by univalent groups.

CHEBI:132717.label: bleaching agent
CHEBI:132717.definition: A reagent that lightens or whitens a substrate through chemical reaction. Bleaching reactions usually involve oxidative or reductive processes that degrade colour systems. Bleaching can occur by destroying one or more of the double bonds in the conjugated chain, by cleaving the conjugated chain, or by oxidation of one of the other moieties in the conjugated chain. Their reactivity results in many bleaches having strong bactericidal, disinfecting, and sterilising properties.

CHEBI:59740.label: nucleophilic reagent
CHEBI:59740.definition: A reagent that forms a bond to its reaction partner (the electrophile) by donating both bonding electrons.

CHEBI:28938.label: ammonium
CHEBI:28938.definition: An onium cation obtained by protonation of ammonia.

CHEBI:35107.label: azane
CHEBI:35107.definition: Saturated acyclic nitrogen hydrides having the general formula NnHn+2.

CHEBI:29340.label: hydridonitrate(2-)
CHEBI:29340.definition: A divalent inorganic anion resulting from the removal of two protons from ammonia.

CHEBI:23924.label: enzyme inhibitor
CHEBI:23924.definition: A compound or agent that combines with an enzyme in such a manner as to prevent the normal substrate-enzyme combination and the catalytic reaction.

CHEBI:28616.label: carbamic acid
CHEBI:28616.definition: A one-carbon compound that is ammonia in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a carboxy group. Although carbamic acid derivatives are common, carbamic acid itself has never been synthesised.

CHEBI:50047.label: organic amino compound
CHEBI:50047.definition: A compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by organyl groups.

CHEBI:35620.label: vasodilator agent
CHEBI:35620.definition: A drug used to cause dilation of the blood vessels.

CHEBI:17544.label: hydrogencarbonate
CHEBI:17544.definition: The carbon oxoanion resulting from the removal of a proton from carbonic acid.

CHEBI:33575.label: carboxylic acid
CHEBI:33575.definition: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one -C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.

CHEBI:39745.label: dihydrogenphosphate
CHEBI:39745.definition: A monovalent inorganic anion that consists of phosphoric acid in which one of the three OH groups has been deprotonated.

CHEBI:43474.label: hydrogenphosphate
CHEBI:43474.definition: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of dihydrogenphosphate.

CHEBI:18367.label: phosphate(3-)
CHEBI:18367.definition: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of hydrogenphosphate.

CHEBI:10545.label: electron
CHEBI:10545.definition: Elementary particle not affected by the strong force having a spin 1/2, a negative elementary charge and a rest mass of 0.000548579903(13) u, or 0.51099906(15) MeV.

CHEBI:33253.label: nucleon
CHEBI:33253.definition: Heavy nuclear particle: proton or neutron.

CHEBI:36339.label: baryon
CHEBI:36339.definition: Baryon is a fermion that does experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek betaalpharhoupsilonsigma (heavy).

CHEBI:36343.label: composite particle
CHEBI:36343.definition: A subatomic particle known to have substructure (i.e. consisting of smaller particles).

CHEBI:36340.label: fermion
CHEBI:36340.definition: Particle of half-integer spin quantum number following Fermi-Dirac statistics. Fermions are named after Enrico Fermi.

CHEBI:33233.label: fundamental particle
CHEBI:33233.definition: A particle not known to have substructure.

CHEBI:36347.label: nuclear particle
CHEBI:36347.definition: A nucleus or any of its constituents in any of their energy states.

CHEBI:36344.label: hadron
CHEBI:36344.definition: Hadron is a subatomic particle which experiences the strong force.

CHEBI:33252.label: atomic nucleus
CHEBI:33252.definition: A nucleus is the positively charged central portion of an atom, excluding the orbital electrons.

CHEBI:37577.label: heteroatomic molecular entity
CHEBI:37577.definition: A molecular entity consisting of two or more chemical elements.

CHEBI:25367.label: molecule
CHEBI:25367.definition: Any polyatomic entity that is an electrically neutral entity consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:33702.label: polyatomic cation
CHEBI:33702.definition: A cation consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:36586.label: carbonyl compound
CHEBI:36586.definition: Any compound containing the carbonyl group, C=O. The term is commonly used in the restricted sense of aldehydes and ketones, although it actually includes carboxylic acids and derivatives.

CHEBI:64641.label: divalent inorganic cation
CHEBI:64641.definition: An inorganic cation with a valency of two.

CHEBI:60242.label: monovalent inorganic cation
CHEBI:60242.definition: An atom or small molecule with a positive charge that does not contain carbon in covalent linkage, with a valency of one.

CHEBI:24866.label: salt
CHEBI:24866.definition: A salt is an assembly of cations and anions.

CHEBI:29347.label: monocarboxylic acid amide
CHEBI:29347.definition: A carboxamide derived from a monocarboxylic acid.

CHEBI:26820.label: sulfates
CHEBI:26820.definition: Salts and esters of sulfuric acid

CHEBI:27207.label: univalent carboacyl group
CHEBI:27207.definition: A univalent carboacyl group is a group formed by loss of OH from the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid.

CHEBI:138103.label: inorganic acid
CHEBI:138103.definition: A Bronsted acid derived from one or more inorganic compounds. Inorganic acids (also known as mineral acids) form hydrons and conjugate base ions when dissolved in water.

CHEBI:48356.label: protic solvent
CHEBI:48356.definition: A polar solvent that is capable of acting as a hydron (proton) donor.

CHEBI:48354.label: polar solvent
CHEBI:48354.definition: A solvent that is composed of polar molecules. Polar solvents can dissolve ionic compounds or ionisable covalent compounds.

CHEBI:62982.label: ammonium dihydrogen phosphate
CHEBI:62982.definition: The ammonium salt of phosphoric acid (molar ratio 1:1).

CHEBI:48379.label: isourea
CHEBI:48379.definition: A carboximidic acid that is the imidic acid tautomer of urea, H2NC(=NH)OH, and its hydrocarbyl derivatives.

CHEBI:50313.label: onium cation
CHEBI:50313.definition: Mononuclear cations derived by addition of a hydron to a mononuclear parent hydride of the pnictogen, chalcogen and halogen families.

CHEBI:33285.label: heteroorganic entity
CHEBI:33285.definition: A heteroorganic entity is an organic molecular entity in which carbon atoms or organic groups are bonded directly to one or more heteroatoms.

CHEBI:64708.label: one-carbon compound
CHEBI:64708.definition: An organic molecular entity containing a single carbon atom (C1).

CHEBI:64709.label: organic acid
CHEBI:64709.definition: Any organic molecular entity that is acidic and contains carbon in covalent linkage.

CHEBI:33232.label: application
CHEBI:33232.definition: Intended use of the molecular entity or part thereof by humans.

CHEBI:24432.label: biological role
CHEBI:24432.definition: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biological context.

CHEBI:51086.label: chemical role
CHEBI:51086.definition: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a chemical context.

CHEBI:15339.label: acceptor
CHEBI:15339.definition: A molecular entity that can accept an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group from another molecular entity.

CHEBI:37527.label: acid
CHEBI:37527.definition: An acid is a molecular entity capable of donating a hydron (Bronsted acid) or capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron pair (Lewis acid).

CHEBI:22695.label: base
CHEBI:22695.definition: A molecular entity having an available pair of electrons capable of forming a covalent bond with a hydron (Bronsted base) or with the vacant orbital of some other molecular entity (Lewis base).

CHEBI:35223.label: catalyst
CHEBI:35223.definition: A substance that increases the rate of a reaction without modifying the overall standard Gibbs energy change in the reaction.

CHEBI:17891.label: donor
CHEBI:17891.definition: A molecular entity that can transfer ("donate") an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group to another molecular entity.

CHEBI:63490.label: explosive
CHEBI:63490.definition: A substance capable of undergoing rapid and highly exothermic decomposition.

CHEBI:76413.label: greenhouse gas
CHEBI:76413.definition: A gas in an atmosphere that absorbs and emits radiation within the thermal infrared range, so contributing to the 'greenhouse effect'.

CHEBI:63248.label: oxidising agent
CHEBI:63248.definition: A substance that removes electrons from another reactant in a redox reaction.

CHEBI:32988.label: amide
CHEBI:32988.definition: An amide is a derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

CHEBI:35276.label: ammonium compound
CHEBI:35276.definition: Compounds (NH4(+))Y(-) and derivatives, in which one or more of the hydrogens bonded to nitrogen have been replaced with univalent groups.

CHEBI:62764.label: reactive nitrogen species
CHEBI:62764.definition: A family of nitrogen molecular entities which are highly reactive and derived from nitric oxide (.NO) and superoxide (O2.(-)) produced via the enzymatic activity of inducible nitric oxide synthase 2 (NOS2) and NADPH oxidase respectively.

CHEBI:51422.label: organodiyl group
CHEBI:51422.definition: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having two free valences at carbon atom(s).

CHEBI:33249.label: organyl group
CHEBI:33249.definition: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having one free valence at a carbon atom.

CHEBI:25212.label: metabolite
CHEBI:25212.definition: Any intermediate or product resulting from metabolism. The term 'metabolite' subsumes the classes commonly known as primary and secondary metabolites.

CHEBI:50902.label: genotoxin
CHEBI:50902.definition: A role played by a chemical compound to induce direct or indirect DNA damage. Such damage can potentially lead to the formation of a malignant tumour, but DNA damage does not lead inevitably to the creation of cancerous cells.

CHEBI:50910.label: neurotoxin
CHEBI:50910.definition: A poison that interferes with the functions of the nervous system.

CHEBI:78295.label: food component
CHEBI:78295.definition: Any substance that is distributed in foodstuffs. It includes materials derived from plants or animals, such as vitamins or minerals, as well as environmental contaminants.

CHEBI:23888.label: drug
CHEBI:23888.definition: Any substance which when absorbed into a living organism may modify one or more of its functions. The term is generally accepted for a substance taken for a therapeutic purpose, but is also commonly used for abused substances.

CHEBI:18219.label: ammonium hydroxide
CHEBI:18219.definition: A solution of ammonia in water.

CHEBI:26078.label: phosphoric acid
CHEBI:26078.definition: A phosphorus oxoacid that consits of one oxo and three hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central phosphorus atom.

CHEBI:60004.label: mixture
CHEBI:60004.definition: A mixture is a chemical substance composed of multiple molecules, at least two of which are of a different kind.

CHEBI:91238.label: calcium ammonium nitrate
CHEBI:91238.definition: A mixture obtained by combining ammonium nitrate, calcium nitrate and water. It is widely used as a nitrogen fertilizer in agriculture.

CHEBI:88276.label: urea ammonium nitrate
CHEBI:88276.definition: A mixture consisting of urea (typically 40-45%), ammonium nitrate (30-35%) and water (30-20%). It is used as a nitrogen fertilizer in agriculture.

CHEBI:64577.label: flour treatment agent
CHEBI:64577.definition: A food additive which is added to flour or dough to improve baking quality and/or colour.

CHEBI:64049.label: food acidity regulator
CHEBI:64049.definition: A food additive that is used to change or otherwise control the acidity or alkalinity of foods. They may be acids, bases, neutralising agents or buffering agents.

CHEBI:77974.label: food packaging gas
CHEBI:77974.definition: A food additive that is a (generally inert) gas which is used to envelop foodstuffs during packing and so protect them from unwanted chemical reactions such as food spoilage or oxidation during subsequent transport and storage. The term includes propellant gases, used to expel foods from a container.

CHEBI:78017.label: food propellant
CHEBI:78017.definition: A propellant that is used to expel foods from an aerosol container.

CHEBI:36587.label: organic oxo compound
CHEBI:36587.definition: Organic compounds containing an oxygen atom, =O, doubly bonded to carbon or another element.

CHEBI:84735.label: algal metabolite
CHEBI:84735.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in algae including unicellular organisms like chlorella and diatoms to multicellular organisms like giant kelps and brown algae.

CHEBI:75767.label: animal metabolite
CHEBI:75767.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in animals that include diverse creatures from sponges, insects to mammals.

CHEBI:76946.label: fungal metabolite
CHEBI:76946.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in fungi, the kingdom that includes microorganisms such as the yeasts and moulds.

CHEBI:83039.label: crustacean metabolite
CHEBI:83039.definition: An animal metabolite produced by arthropods such as crabs, lobsters, crayfish, shrimps and krill.

CHEBI:75768.label: mammalian metabolite
CHEBI:75768.definition: Any animal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in mammals.

CHEBI:77746.label: human metabolite
CHEBI:77746.definition: Any mammalian metabolite  produced during a metabolic reaction in humans (Homo sapiens).

CHEBI:75771.label: mouse metabolite
CHEBI:75771.definition: Any mammalian metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in a mouse (Mus musculus).

CHEBI:76969.label: bacterial metabolite
CHEBI:76969.definition: Any prokaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in bacteria.

CHEBI:76764.label: EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor
CHEBI:76764.definition: Any hydrolase inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase acting on C-N bonds, other than peptide bonds (EC 3.5.*.*).

CHEBI:76807.label: EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor
CHEBI:76807.definition: An EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase (EC 3.5.1.*).

CHEBI:77941.label: EC 3.5.1.4 (amidase) inhibitor
CHEBI:77941.definition: An EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of amidase (EC 3.5.1.4).

CHEBI:75772.label: Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite
CHEBI:75772.definition: Any  fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Baker's yeast (Saccharomyces cerevisiae).

CHEBI:76971.label: Escherichia coli metabolite
CHEBI:76971.definition: Any bacterial metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Escherichia coli.

CHEBI:33284.label: nutrient
CHEBI:33284.definition: A nutrient is a food component that an organism uses to survive and grow.

CHEBI:15138.label: sulfide(2-)
CHEBI:15138.definition: A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of both protons from hydrogen sulfide.

CHEBI:83057.label: Daphnia metabolite
CHEBI:83057.definition: A crustacean metabolite produced by the genus of small planktonic arthropods, Daphnia

CHEBI:83056.label: Daphnia magna metabolite
CHEBI:83056.definition: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia magna.

ENVO:00000002.label: anthropogenic geographic feature
ENVO:00000002.definition:
An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature
resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.

ENVO:01001308.label: hydroform
ENVO:01001308.definition: A hydroform is a geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid water held in shape by an environmental process.

ENVO:00000012.label: hydrographic feature
ENVO:00000012.definition: A geographical feature associated with water.

ENVO:00000098.label: island
ENVO:00000098.definition: Area of dry or relatively dry land surrounded by water or low wetland.

ENVO:01000281.label: layer
ENVO:01000281.definition: A layer is a quantity of some material which has comparable thickness and usually covers some surface.

ENVO:00000063.label: water body
ENVO:00000063.definition: An accumulation of water of varying size.
ENVO:00000063.synonyms: bodies of water;waterbody;aquatic feature;body of water

ENVO:01000755.label: aeroform
ENVO:01000755.definition: An aeroform is a geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of gaseous or aerosolised material held in shape by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:01000687.label: coast
ENVO:01000687.definition: A coast is the area where land meets the sea, ocean, or lake.

ENVO:03000110.label: cryoform
ENVO:03000110.definition: A geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous mass of snow and/or ice.

ENVO:00000077.label: agricultural feature
ENVO:00000077.synonyms: bailing station;irrigated field;grazing allotment;stockyard;pastoral site;nursery;dairy;sheepfold;cattle dipping tank;corral;feedlot;grange;barn

ENVO:00000070.label: construction
ENVO:00000070.definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

ENVO:00000046.label: hedge
ENVO:00000046.definition: A dense growth of shrubbery planted as a fence or boundary.

ENVO:00000026.label: well
ENVO:00000026.definition: A cylindrical hole, pit, or tunnel drilled or dug down to a depth from which water, oil, or gas can be pumped or brought to the surface.

ENVO:00000005.label: first-order administrative region
ENVO:00000005.definition: A primary administrative division of a country, such as a state in the United States.

ENVO:00000123.label: political entity
ENVO:00000123.definition: A geographical region whose affairs and population are administered by an authority.

ENVO:00000006.label: second-order administrative region
ENVO:00000006.definition: A subdivision of a first-order administrative division.

ENVO:00000007.label: third-order administrative region
ENVO:00000007.definition: A subdivision of a second-order administrative division.

ENVO:00000501.label: bed
ENVO:00000501.definition: The portion of the ground surface which lies below water.

ENVO:00000475.label: inlet
ENVO:00000475.definition: An opening of the sea into the land, or of a lake into its shore.

ENVO:00000093.label: lacustrine beach
ENVO:00000093.definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a lake.

ENVO:00000178.label: levee
ENVO:00000178.definition: An artificial slope or wall, usually earthen, which parallels the course of a river, built for the purpose of containing the river.

ENVO:01000044.label: marine pelagic feature
ENVO:01000044.definition: A prominent or distinctive aspect, quality, or characteristic of environments occurring within the marine water column.

ENVO:00000130.label: reef
ENVO:00000130.definition: A ridge of rocks, lying near the surface of the sea, which may be visible at low tide, but is usually covered by water.
ENVO:00000130.synonyms: REEF;barrier reef;shore reef;fringing reef;bank reef;submerged reef;atoll reef

ENVO:00000017.label: saline hydrographic feature
ENVO:00000017.definition: A geographical feature associated with water with a halinity above 30 ppt (roughly 35 g/L).

ENVO:00000092.label: sea beach
ENVO:00000092.definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a sea.

ENVO:00000304.label: shore
ENVO:00000304.definition: That part of the land in immediate contact with a body of water including the area between high and low water lines.

ENVO:00000019.label: saline lake
ENVO:00000019.definition: A lake whose water contains a considerable concentration of dissolved salts.

ENVO:01001062.label: crater lake
ENVO:01001062.definition: A lake contained within a crater.

ENVO:01001022.label: natural lake
ENVO:01001022.definition: A lake which has formed as the result of processes that are not or are only minimally driven by human activity.

ENVO:01000297.label: freshwater river
ENVO:01000297.definition: A river where fresh water flows.

ENVO:00000450.label: irrigation reservoir
ENVO:00000450.definition: A reservoir constructed for the purpose of providing water for irrigation.

ENVO:00000023.label: stream
ENVO:00000023.definition: Linear body of water flowing on the Earth's surface.

ENVO:00000230.label: coastal wetland
ENVO:00000230.definition: A wetland associated with the part of the land adjoining or near a sea or ocean.

ENVO:00000243.label: freshwater wetland
ENVO:00000243.definition: A wetland whose water that contains low concentrations of salts.

ENVO:00000233.label: swamp
ENVO:00000233.definition: A wetland that features permanent inundation of large areas of land by shallow bodies of water, generally with a substantial number of hummocks, or dry-land protrusions.

AGRO:00000009.label: irrigation source
AGRO:00000009.definition: A water body from which water is taken during an irrigation process and transported to the target of the irrigation process.

ENVO:01000617.label: lentic water body
ENVO:01000617.definition: A lentic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, has very little to no directed flow.

ENVO:01000618.label: lotic water body
ENVO:01000618.definition: A lotic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, is flowing.

ENVO:00000078.label: farm
ENVO:00000078.definition: A tract of crop or grazing land, as well as the group of buildings with and often surrounding a farmhouse, including barns, sheds, and other outbuildings, used for agricultural production.

ENVO:00000117.label: plantation
ENVO:00000117.definition: An intentional planting of a crop, on a large scale, usually for uses other than cereal production or pasture. The term is currently most often used for plantings of trees and shrubs. The term tends also to be used for plantings maintained on economic bases other than that of subsistence farming.

AGRO:00000391.label: field margin
AGRO:00000391.definition:
Strips of land along the borders of crop fields. It also include vegetative strips adjacent
to roads, paths, railways, hedgerows and forest boundaries.

ENVO:00000090.label: coastal plain
ENVO:00000090.definition: An area of flat, low-lying land adjacent to a coast and separated from the interior by other features.

ENVO:00000255.label: flood plain
ENVO:00000255.definition: An area which is subject to periodic flooding.

ENVO:00000312.label: sandur
ENVO:00000312.definition: The plain formed by the large amounts of silt and sediment, picked up as a glacier erodes the underlying rocks as it moves slowly downhill, and at the snout of the glacier, meltwater can carry this sediment away from the glacier and deposit it on a broad plain. The material in the outwash plain is often size-sorted by the water runoff of the melting glacier with the finest materials, like silt, being the most distantly re-deposited, whereas larger boulders are the closest to the original terminus of the glacier.

ENVO:00000222.label: oceanic island
ENVO:00000222.definition: An island that does not sit on a continental shelf, and is of volcanic origin.

ENVO:00000247.label: volcano
ENVO:00000247.definition: An opening, or rupture, in the Earth's surface or crust, which allows hot, molten rock, ash and gases to escape from deep below the surface.

ENVO:00000424.label: lake island
ENVO:00000424.definition: An island that lies in a lake.

ENVO:00000423.label: river island
ENVO:00000423.definition: An island that lies in a river.

ENVO:00000248.label: glacial valley
ENVO:00000248.definition: A valley that contains, or contained, a glacier and was formed by glacial activity. Typically U-shaped in cross-section.

ENVO:00000129.label: stream valley
ENVO:00000129.definition: A valley that contains, and has been formed by, a stream.

ENVO:00000108.label: meadow
ENVO:00000108.definition: A habitat of rolling or flat terrain where grasses predominate. Typically, what is called a meadow has more biodiversity than a grassland as the former contains not only grasses but a significant variety of annual, biennial and perennial plants.

ENVO:00000266.label: pasture
ENVO:00000266.definition: Grassland used for grazing of ungulate livestock as part of a farm or ranch.

ENVO:00000260.label: prairie
ENVO:00000260.definition: An area of land of low topographic relief that historically supported grasses and herbs, with few trees, and having generally a mesic (moderate or temperate) climate. Dominated by tall grasses (contrast steppe).

ENVO:00000261.label: savanna
ENVO:00000261.definition: A grassland of the tropics or subtropics with scattered trees.

ENVO:00000262.label: steppe
ENVO:00000262.definition: A plain without trees (apart from those near rivers and lakes); it is similar to a prairie, although a prairie is generally considered as being dominated by tall grasses, while short grasses are said to be normal in the steppe. It may be semi-desert, or covered with grass or shrubs or both, depending on the season and latitude.

ENVO:00000111.label: forest
ENVO:00000111.definition: An area with a high density of trees. A small forest may be called a wood.

ENVO:00000119.label: planted forest
ENVO:00000119.definition: A forest that has been intentionally established by human intervention.

ENVO:01000376.label: tropical marine semi-evergreen forest
ENVO:01000376.definition: A semi-evergreen forest is a forest which undergoes a long dry season and, as a consequence, has a two-storey layer structure,  a dry canopy, a leaf litter layer that only decays during moist periods trees with very small leaves or which shed their leaves to conserve water and which flower during the dry season and grow during the wet season.

ENVO:01000768.label: primary forest
ENVO:01000768.definition: Forest which originally covered a region before changes in the environment brought about by people. (Source: PHC)

ENVO:00000297.label: paddy field
ENVO:00000297.definition: A flooded parcel of arable land used for growing rice and other semiaquatic crops.

AGRO:00000390.label: fallow land
AGRO:00000390.definition: An agricultural field that is set aside for a period of time before it is cultivated again; or an agricultral field that is under permanent crops, meadows or pastures and that is not being used for such purposes for a period of at least one year.

ENVO:00000009.label: national geopolitical entity
ENVO:00000009.definition: A political association with effective dominion over a geographic area.
ENVO:00000009.synonyms: nation;independent nation;independent political entity;independent sovereign nation

ENVO:01000406.label: snow
ENVO:01000406.definition: Snow is an environmental material which is primarily composed of flakes of crystalline water ice.

ENVO:00000393.label: sound
ENVO:00000393.definition: A large sea or ocean inlet larger than a bay, deeper than a bight, wider than a fjord, or it may identify a narrow sea or ocean channel between two bodies of land.

ENVO:00000142.label: stream bank
ENVO:00000142.definition: The sloping margin of a stream, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

ENVO:00000143.label: river bank
ENVO:00000143.definition: The sloping margin of a river, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

ENVO:00000287.label: butte
ENVO:00000287.definition: An isolated hill with steep sides and a small flat top, smaller than mesas and plateaus. Buttes are formed by erosion when a cap of hard rock, usually of volcanic origin, covers a layer of softer rock that is easily worn away. This hard rock avoids erosion while the rock around it wears down.

ENVO:00000542.label: kame
ENVO:00000542.definition: An irregularly shaped hill or mound composed of sorted or stratified sand and gravel that is deposited in contact with the glacial ice. It can have an irregular shape. Kames are often associated with kettles, and this is referred to as kame and kettle topography. When the ice retreats further, the delta kame often collapses. Kame terraces are frequently found along the side of a glacial valley and are the deposits of meltwater streams flowing between the ice and the adjacent valley side.

ENVO:00000097.label: desert
ENVO:00000097.definition: A region rendered barren or partially barren by environmental extremes, especially by low rainfall.

ENVO:00000176.label: elevation
ENVO:00000176.definition: A landform elevated above the surrounding area.

ENVO:00000508.label: terrace
ENVO:00000508.definition: A step-like feature between higher and lower ground: a relatively flat or gently inclined shelf of earth, backed and fronted by steep slopes or manmade detaining walls.

AGRO:00000339.label: agronomic land element
AGRO:00000339.definition: Description of the geomorphology of the immediate surroundings of the experimental site.

ENVO:01000667.label: geological fracture
ENVO:01000667.definition: A geological fracture is any separation in a geologic formation, such as a joint or a fault that divides a mass of rock into two or more pieces.

AGRO:00000338.label: higher-level landform
AGRO:00000338.definition: The landform refers to the shape of the land surface in the area in which the agronomic trial site is located.

ENVO:00000166.label: atoll
ENVO:00000166.definition: An oceanic island, often having a characteristic ring-like shape surrounding a lagoon. Atolls are formed when coral reef grows around a volcanic island that later subsides into the ocean.

ENVO:01000328.label: dome swamp
ENVO:01000328.definition: A dome swamp is a swamp which occurs in a depression where deeper waters at the centre of the swamp allow  trees to grow taller relative to those in shallower regions of the depression. This creates a dome-like shape.

ENVO:00000184.label: hanging valley
ENVO:00000184.definition: A tributary valley with the floor at a higher relief than the main channel into which it flows. They are most commonly associated with U-shaped valleys when a tributary glacier flows into a glacier of larger volume.

ENVO:00000529.label: beach ridge
ENVO:00000529.definition: A ridge of sand just inland and parallel to the beach, usually in series.

ENVO:00000485.label: sea shore
ENVO:00000485.definition: That part of the land in immediate contact with a sea, including the intertidal zone.

ENVO:00000395.label: channel of a watercourse
ENVO:00000395.definition: The physical confine of a river, slough or ocean strait consisting of a bed and banks.

ENVO:00000514.label: crater
ENVO:00000514.definition: A generally circular saucer or bowl-shaped depression caused by volcanic or meteorite explosive action.

ENVO:00000291.label: drainage basin
ENVO:00000291.definition: An extent or area of land where surface water from rain and melting snow or ice converges to a single point at lower elevation, usually the exit of the basin, where the waters join another waterbody.

ENVO:00000311.label: kettle
ENVO:00000311.definition: A fluvioglacial landform occurring as the result of blocks of ice calving from the front of a receding glacier and becoming partially to wholly buried by glacial outwash. Glacial outwash is generated when sediment laden streams of meltwater flow away from the glacier and are deposited to form broad outwash plains called sandurs. When the ice blocks melt, holes are left in the sandur.

ENVO:03000015.label: geographic basin
ENVO:03000015.definition: A depression which is part of a planetary crust, is of geographic scale, and is partially or completely enclosed.

ENVO:00000341.label: piece of gravel
ENVO:00000341.definition: A piece of rock that is two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension (about 1/12 of an inch) and no more than 75 millimeters (about 3 inches).

ENVO:00000025.label: reservoir
ENVO:00000025.definition: An artificial body of water, often contained by a dam, constructed for the purpose of water storage.

ENVO:00000446.label: terrestrial biome
ENVO:00000446.definition: A biome that applies to the terrestrial realm.

ENVO:01000179.label: desert biome
ENVO:01000179.definition: A desert biome is a terrestrial biome which loses more liquid water by evapotranspiration than is supplied by precipitation and includes communities adapted to these conditions.

ENVO:01000181.label: mangrove biome
ENVO:01000181.definition: A mangrove biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, mangrove plants (Rhizophoraceae). Mangrove plants are able to withstand high levels of salinity as well as regions of anoxia and frequent tidal inundation. Mangrove biomes often occur near tropical and sub-tropical estuaries and depositional marine coastal environments where fine sediments (often with high organic content) collect in areas protected from high energy wave action.

ENVO:00000137.label: coastal inlet
ENVO:00000137.definition: An opening of the sea into the land.

ENVO:00000476.label: lake inlet
ENVO:00000476.definition: An opening of a lake into its shore.

ENVO:00000433.label: kame terrace
ENVO:00000433.definition: A terrace associated with a kame.

ENVO:00002016.label: sedimentary rock
ENVO:00002016.definition: A rock formed by deposition of either clastic sediments, organic matter, or chemical precipitates (evaporites), followed by compaction of the particulate matter and cementation during diagenesis.

ENVO:00002015.label: volcanic rock
ENVO:00002015.definition: An igneous rock that results from magma reaching the surface either as lava or fragmental ejecta.

ENVO:00002234.label: acrisol
ENVO:00002234.definition: Acrisols are soils that have a higher clay content in the subsoil than in the topsoil as a result of pedogenetic processes (especially clay migration) leading to an argic subsoil horizon. Acrisols have in certain depths a low base saturation and low-activity clays.

ENVO:00002232.label: andosol
ENVO:00002232.definition: Andosols are soils that develop in volcanic ejecta or glasses under almost any climate (except under hyperarid climate conditions). However, Andosols may also develop in other silicate-rich materials under acid weathering in humid and perhumid climates.

ENVO:00002229.label: arenosol
ENVO:00002229.definition: Arenosols are sandy soils, including both soils developed in residual sands after in situ weathering of usually quartz-rich sediments or rock, and soils developed in recently deposited sands such as dunes in deserts and beach lands.

ENVO:00002235.label: cambisol
ENVO:00002235.definition: Cambisols combine soils with at least an incipient subsurface soil formation. Transformation of parent material is evident from structure formation and mostly brownish discoloration, increasing clay percentage, and/or carbonate removal.

ENVO:00002237.label: chernozem
ENVO:00002237.definition: Chernozems are soils with a thick black surface layer that is rich in organic matter.

ENVO:00003082.label: enriched soil
ENVO:00003082.definition: A portion of enriched soil is a portion of soil with elevated levels of some material entity.

ENVO:00002246.label: ferralsol
ENVO:00002246.definition: Ferralsols represent the classical, deeply weathered, red or yellow soils of the humid tropics. These soils have diffuse horizon boundaries, a clay assemblage dominated by low-activity clays (mainly kaolinite) and a high content of sesquioxides.

ENVO:00002273.label: fluvisol
ENVO:00002273.definition: Fluvisols accommodate genetically young, azonal soils in alluvial deposits.

ENVO:00002244.label: gleysol
ENVO:00002244.definition: Gleysols are wetland soils that, unless drained, are saturated with groundwater for long enough periods to develop a characteristic gleyic colour pattern. This pattern is essentially made up of reddish, brownish or yellowish colours at ped surfaces and/or in the upper soil layer or layers, in combination with greyish/bluish colours inside the peds and/or deeper in the soil.

ENVO:00002245.label: gypsisol
ENVO:00002245.definition: Gypsisols are soils with substantial secondary accumulation of gypsum (calcium sulfate). These soils are found in the driest parts of the arid climate zone.

ENVO:00002243.label: histosol
ENVO:00002243.definition: Histosols comprise soils formed in organic material. These vary from soils developed in predominantly moss peat in boreal, arctic and subarctic regions, via moss peat, reeds/ sedge peat (fen) and forest peat in temperate regions to mangrove peat and swamp forest peat in the humid tropics. Histosols are found at all altitudes, but the vast majority occurs in lowlands.

ENVO:00002240.label: kastanozem
ENVO:00002240.definition: Kastanozems are dry grassland soils, among them the zonal soils of the short-grass steppe belt, south of the Eurasian tall-grass steppe belt with Chernozems. Kastanozems have a similar profile to that of Chernozems but the humus-rich surface horizon is thinner and not as dark as that of the Chernozems and they show more prominent accumulation of secondary carbonates.

ENVO:00002248.label: luvisol
ENVO:00002248.definition: Luvisols are soils that have a higher clay content in the subsoil than in the topsoil as a result of pedogenetic processes (especially clay migration) leading to an argic subsoil horizon. Luvisols have high-activity clays throughout the argic horizon and a high base saturation at certain depths.

ENVO:00002247.label: nitisol
ENVO:00002247.definition: Nitisols are deep, well-drained, red, tropical soils with diffuse horizon boundaries and a subsurface horizon with more than 30 percent clay and moderate to strong angular blocky structure elements that easily fall apart into characteristic shiny, polyhedric (nutty) elements. Weathering is relatively advanced but Nitisols are far more productive than most other red, tropical soils.

ENVO:00000134.label: permafrost
ENVO:00000134.definition: Soil at or below the freezing point of water (0C or 32F) for two or more years. Ice is not always present, as may be in the case of nonporous bedrock, but it frequently occurs and it may be in amounts exceeding the potential hydraulic saturation of the ground material.

ENVO:00002249.label: phaeozem
ENVO:00002249.definition: Phaeozems accommodate soils of relatively wet grassland and forest regions in moderately continental climates. Phaeozems are much like Chernozems and Kastanozems but are leached more intensively. Consequently, they have dark, humus rich surface horizons that, in comparison with Chernozems and Kastanozems, are less rich in bases. Phaeozems may or may not have secondary carbonates but have a high base saturation in the upper metre of the soil.

ENVO:00002257.label: podzol
ENVO:00002257.definition: Podzols are soils with a typically ash-grey upper subsurface horizon, bleached by loss of organic matter and iron oxides, on top of a dark accumulation horizon with brown, reddish or black illuviated humus and/or reddish Fe compounds. Podzols occur in humid areas in the boreal and temperate zones and locally also in the tropics.

ENVO:00002256.label: regosol
ENVO:00002256.definition: Regosols form a taxonomic remnant group containing all soils that could not be accommodated in any of the other RSGs. In practice, Regosols are very weakly developed mineral soils in unconsolidated materials that do not have a mollic or umbric horizon, are not very shallow or very rich in gravels (Leptosols), sandy (Arenosols) or with fluvic materials (Fluvisols). Regosols are extensive in eroding lands, particularly in arid and semi-arid areas and in mountainous terrain.

ENVO:00002252.label: solonchak
ENVO:00002252.definition: Solonchaks are soils that have a high concentration of soluble salts at some time in the year. Solonchaks are largely confined to the arid and semi-arid climate zones and to coastal regions in all climates.

ENVO:00002255.label: solonetz
ENVO:00002255.definition: Solonetz are soils with a dense, strongly structured, clayey subsurface horizon that has a high proportion of adsorbed Na and/or Mg ions. Solonetz that contain free soda (Na2CO3) are strongly alkaline (field pH > 8.5).

ENVO:00002254.label: vertisol
ENVO:00002254.definition: A soil in which there is a high content of expansive clay known as montmorillonite that forms deep cracks in drier seasons or years. Alternate shrinking and swelling causes self-mulching, where the soil material consistently mixes itself, causing vertisols to have an extremely deep A horizon and no B horizon.

ENVO:02000049.label: coastal water body
ENVO:02000049.definition: Coastal water is a marine water body bordering a coast.

ENVO:00000015.label: ocean
ENVO:00000015.definition: Continuous saline-water bodies that surround the continents and fill the Earth's great depressions.

ENVO:00000016.label: sea
ENVO:00000016.definition: A large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean.
ENVO:00000016.synonyms: sea;Sea;open sea;open water;channel;open sound;marginal sea;closed sea

ENVO:00000141.label: bank
ENVO:00000141.definition: The sloping margin of a watercourse, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

ENVO:00000280.label: escarpment
ENVO:00000280.definition: A transition zone between different physiogeographic provinces that involves an elevation differential, often involving high cliffs. Most commonly a transition from one series of sedimentary rocks to another series of a different age and composition. In such cases, the escarpment usually represents the line of erosional loss of the newer rock over the older.

ENVO:01000332.label: gravelly slope
ENVO:01000332.definition: A gravelly slope is a slope which has a surface primarily composed of gravel.

ENVO:01000333.label: hillside
ENVO:01000333.definition: A hillside is a slope that is part of a hill.

ENVO:01000319.label: rocky slope
ENVO:01000319.definition: A rocky slope is a slope which has a surface primarily composed of rock.

ENVO:01000334.label: talus slope
ENVO:01000334.definition: A talus slope is a slope which has a surface layer composed of scree.

ENVO:00002011.label: fresh water
ENVO:00002011.definition: Water which has a low concentration of dissolved solutes, particularly that of sodium chloride.

ENVO:00002010.label: saline water
ENVO:00002010.definition: Water which contains a significant concentration of dissolved salts.

ENVO:00002149.label: sea water
ENVO:00002149.definition: Water which has physicochemical properties that have been determined by the processes occuring in a sea or ocean.

ENVO:00000447.label: marine biome
ENVO:00000447.definition: An aquatic biome that comprises systems of open-ocean and unprotected coastal habitats, characterized by exposure to wave action, tidal fluctuation, and ocean currents as well as systems that largely resemble these. Water in the marine biome is generally within the salinity range of seawater: 30 to 38 ppt.

ENVO:00002150.label: coastal sea water
ENVO:00002150.definition: Coastal sea water is sea water that is adjacent to a coast.
ENVO:00002150.synonyms: coastal oceanic water;coastal seawater;coastal ocean water

AGRO:00000091.label: spent mushroom compost
AGRO:00000091.definition: A compost that contains the residual compost waste generated by mushroom production. It  generally consists of a combination of wheat straw, dried blood, horse manure and ground chalk, composted together.

ENVO:00002872.label: bagasse
ENVO:00002872.definition: The biomass remaining after sugarcane stalks are crushed to extract their juice.

ENVO:01000408.label: environmental zone
ENVO:01000408.definition: An environmental zone is an environmental feature whose extent is determined by the presence or influence of one or more material entities or processes. An environmental zone may, itself, assume the role of an environmental feature.

ENVO:00000131.label: glacial feature
ENVO:00000131.definition: A hydrographic feature characterized by the dominance of snow or ice.

ENVO:00002004.label: mesoscopic physical object
ENVO:00002004.definition: An environmental feature that is, or can be, contained and is predominantly composed of one or a few types of stuff.

AGRO:00000384.label: Vegetation maintained on an experimental field
AGRO:00000384.definition: Vegetation maintained in purpose on and at the border of an agronomic experimental field.

ENVO:01000813.label: astronomical body part
ENVO:01000813.definition: A material part of an astronomical body.

ENVO:01000804.label: astronomical object
ENVO:01000804.definition: An object which is composed of one or more gravitationally bound structures that are associated with a position in space.

ENVO:01000637.label: outer space
ENVO:01000637.definition: Outer space is a hard vacuum containing a low density of particles, predominantly a plasma of hydrogen and helium as well as electromagnetic radiation, magnetic fields, neutrinos, dust and cosmic rays that exists between celestial bodies.

AGRO:00000387.label: vegetation surronding an experimental site
AGRO:00000387.definition: Type of vegetation surrounding an agronomic experimental site

ENVO:00003074.label: manufactured product
ENVO:00003074.definition: A material entity that has been processed by humans or their technology in any way, including intermediate products as well as final products.

ENVO:0010001.label: anthropogenic environmental material
ENVO:0010001.definition: Anthropogenic material in or on which organisms may live.

ENVO:00002982.label: clay
ENVO:00002982.definition: A group of hydrous aluminium phyllosilicate (phyllosilicates being a subgroup of silicate minerals) minerals (see clay minerals), that are typically less than 2 micrometres in diameter. Clay consists of a variety of phyllosilicate minerals rich in silicon and aluminium oxides and hydroxides which include variable amounts of structural water.

ENVO:01000018.label: gravel
ENVO:01000018.definition: Gravel is an environmental material which is composed of pieces of rock that are at least two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension and no more than 75 millimeters.

ENVO:01000231.label: lava
ENVO:01000231.definition: Lava is a mixture of molten or semi-molten rock, volatiles, and solids which has extruded beyond a planetary crust.

ENVO:01000155.label: organic material
ENVO:01000155.definition: Environmental material derived from living organisms.

ENVO:01000017.label: sand
ENVO:01000017.definition: A naturally occurring granular material composed of finely divided rock and mineral particles.

ENVO:00000194.label: scree
ENVO:00000194.definition: Broken rock that appears at the bottom of crags, mountain cliffs or valley shoulders.

ENVO:01000016.label: silt
ENVO:01000016.definition: Silt is granular material of a size somewhere between sand and clay whose mineral origin is quartz and feldspar.

ENVO:00001998.label: soil
ENVO:00001998.definition: Soil is an environmental material which is primarily composed of minerals, varying proportions of sand, silt, and clay, organic material such as humus, gases, liquids, and a broad range of resident micro- and macroorganisms.

ENVO:00002264.label: waste material
ENVO:00002264.definition: A material which is not the desired output of a process and which is typically the input of a process which removes it from its producer (e.g. a disposal process).

AGRO:00000090.label: alfalfa meal
AGRO:00000090.definition: An agricultural environmental material that contains ground dry alfalfa.

AGRO:00000079.label: animal manure
AGRO:00000079.definition: Organic matter mostly derived from animal feces which can be used as organic fertilizer in agriculture.

AGRO:00000086.label: blood meal
AGRO:00000086.definition: Dry, inert powder made from blood. Blood usually comes from cattle or hogs as a slaughterhouse by-product.

ENVO:01000797.label: gaseous environmental material
ENVO:01000797.definition: A material entity which is composed of one or more chemical entities and has neither independent shape nor volume but tends to expand indefinitely.

AGRO:00000075.label: green manure
AGRO:00000075.definition: Plants that are grown to be tilled, or cut down to lay on top of the ground for the purpose of adding organic matter and nutrients to the soil.

ENVO:01001125.label: ice
ENVO:01001125.definition: An ice is an environmental material which is either frozen or which is maintained in a solid state by gravitational forces or pressure.

AGRO:00000197.label: liming material
AGRO:00000197.definition: An environmental material containing calcium and/or magnesium compounds  and applied to soil in order to neutralize soil acidity.

ENVO:01000648.label: magma
ENVO:01000648.definition: Magma is a mixture of molten or semi-molten rock, volatiles, and solids that is found beneath the uppermost solid layer of a planetary body. Besides molten rock, magma may also contain suspended crystals, dissolved gas and sometimes gas bubbles.

ENVO:01000853.label: marl
ENVO:01000853.definition: Marl is a mass of calcium carbonate derived from mollusk shells and mixed with silt and clay.

ENVO:01001069.label: metallic material
ENVO:01001069.definition: A material which is composed primarily of one or more pure metals and which shows their properties.

AGRO:00000092.label: mulch
AGRO:00000092.definition: Layer of material applied to the soil surface to conserve moisture, improve soil fertility, reduce weed growth, or enhance the visual appeal of the area.

AGRO:00000085.label: oil cake
AGRO:00000085.definition: The biomass remaining after pressing oil seeds to extract oil.

AGRO:00000088.label: oil meal
AGRO:00000088.definition: An agricultural environmental material that contains ground-biomass remaining after pressing oil seeds.

ENVO:01000060.label: particulate matter
ENVO:01000060.definition: Particulate material is an environmental material which is composed of microscopic portions of solid or liquid material suspended in another environmental material.

ENVO:01000660.label: tephra
ENVO:01000660.definition: Tephra is fragmental material produced by a volcanic eruption regardless of composition, fragment size or emplacement mechanism.

ENVO:01001154.label: volatile astrogeological material
ENVO:01001154.definition: A material which is composed primarily of chemical elements and compounds with relatively low boiling points, equilibrium condensation temperatures below 1300 Kelvin, and which are part of the crust or atmosphere of a moon or planet.

ENVO:01000324.label: planetary surface
ENVO:01000324.definition: A planetary surface is a surface layer where the solid or liquid material of a planet comes into contact with atmosphere or outer space.

ENVO:01001088.label: liquid aerosol
ENVO:01001088.definition: An aerosol which is primarily composed of liquid droplets.

ENVO:01001089.label: solid aerosol
ENVO:01001089.definition: An aerosol which is primarily composed of solid particles.

ENVO:00002170.label: compost
ENVO:00002170.definition: The aerobically decomposed remnants of organic materials.

ENVO:00002869.label: hay
ENVO:00002869.definition: Hay is grass, legumes or other herbaceous plants that have been cut, dried, and stored for use as animal fodder, particularly for grazing livestock such as cattle, horses, goats, and sheep.

ENVO:00003030.label: silage
ENVO:00003030.definition: A fermented, high-moisture forage that can be fed to ruminants.

ENVO:00003869.label: straw
ENVO:00003869.definition: An agricultural byproduct, the dry stalk of a cereal plant, after the nutrient grain or seed has been removed.

AGRO:00000087.label: bagasse
AGRO:00000087.definition: The biomass remaining after sugarcane stalks are crushed to extract their juice.

ENVO:02000055.label: plant feed
ENVO:02000055.definition: Plant feed is a biotic mesoscopic physical object consisting of any foodstuff that is used specifically to feed plants.

ENVO:00000339.label: piece of rock
ENVO:00000339.definition: An abiotic  mesoscopic feature made of the mineral material of the crust of the Earth.

ENVO:00010505.label: aerosol
ENVO:00010505.definition: Airborne solid particles (also called dust or particulate matter (PM)) or liquid droplets.

ENVO:01000560.label: charcoal
ENVO:01000560.definition: Charcoal is a light, black residue, consisting of carbon and any remaining ash, obtained by removing water and other volatile constituents from animal and vegetation substances. Charcoal is usually produced by slow pyrolysis, the heating of wood or other substances in the absence of oxygen.

ENVO:01000230.label: arid
ENVO:01000230.definition: An environmental condition in which annual precipitation is less than half of annual potential evapotranspiration.

ENVO:01000204.label: tropical
ENVO:01000204.definition: A tropical condition is an environmental condition in which an environmental system receives high yearly solar irradiance per unit area and, on Earth, the Sun reaches a subsolar point at least once during the solar year. This results in a hot and moist year-round climate at low elevations, which have a monthly average temperature above 18 degrees Celsius.

ENVO:01000375.label: tropical marine condition
ENVO:01000375.definition: A tropical marine condition is a tropical condition in which the ocean strongly influences the climate and a wet and dry season occur.

ENVO:2100000.label: anatomical entity environment
ENVO:2100000.definition: An environment which is determined by an anatomical entity.

ENVO:01000313.label: anthropogenic environment
ENVO:01000313.definition: An anthropogenic environment is an environmental system which is the product of human activity.

ENVO:01000303.label: endolithic environment
ENVO:01000303.definition: An endolithic environment is an environment that exists within solid rock.

ENVO:01000320.label: marine environment
ENVO:01000320.definition: A marine environment and enviroment which is determined by a marine water body.

ENVO:01001110.label: ecosystem
ENVO:01001110.definition: An environmental system which includes both living and non-living components.

ENVO:01001057.label: environment associated with a plant part or small plant
ENVO:01001057.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead plant, or a whole small plant.

ENVO:01001055.label: environment associated with an animal part or small animal
ENVO:01001055.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead animal, or a whole small animal.

ENVO:01000998.label: environmental system determined by a material
ENVO:01000998.definition: An environmental system within which an environmental material strongly influences the system's composition and properties.

ENVO:01000997.label: environmental system determined by a quality
ENVO:01000997.definition: An environmental system which is determined by materials bearing roughly homogeneous qualities.

ENVO:01000951.label: natural environment
ENVO:01000951.definition: An environmental system in which minimal to no anthropisation has occurred and non-human agents are the primary determinants of the system's dynamics and composition.

ENVO:01000268.label: atmospheric water vapour
ENVO:01000268.definition: Atmospheric water vapour is water vapour that is part of an atmosphere.

ENVO:01000325.label: aquatic layer
ENVO:01000325.definition: A layer in a water mass, itself composed primarily of water.

ENVO:01000267.label: atmosphere
ENVO:01000267.definition: An atmosphere is a layer of gases surrounding a material body of sufficient mass that is held in place by the gravity of the body.

ENVO:00010504.label: surface layer
ENVO:00010504.definition: A surface layer is the uppermost layer of some material entity.

ENVO:01000544.label: boundary layer
ENVO:01000544.definition: A boundary layer is a layer of fluid in the immediate vicinity of a bounding surface where the effects of viscosity are significant enough to distort the surrounding non-viscous flow.

ENVO:01000639.label: planetary structural layer
ENVO:01000639.definition: A planetary structural layer is laminar part of a terrestrial planet or other rocky body large enough to have differentiation by density. Planetary layers have differing physicochemical properties and composition.

ENVO:01000321.label: sea water environment
ENVO:01000321.definition: An environmental system determined by seawater.

ENVO:01001040.label: saline environment
ENVO:01001040.definition: An environment which is determined by materials which bear significant concentrations of salts.

ENVO:01000306.label: freshwater environment
ENVO:01000306.definition: An aquatic environment which is determined by freshwater.

ENVO:01000307.label: saline water environment
ENVO:01000307.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by saline water.

ENVO:01000635.label: land
ENVO:01000635.definition: Land is a planetary surface that is not covered by liquid.

AGRO:00000301.label: agricultural experimental plot
AGRO:00000301.definition: A site within which an agricultural experimental process is conducted

AGRO:00000303.label: block
AGRO:00000303.definition: A block is a relatively large area or several identical units receiving all or most of the treatments. A collection of plots is called a block.

AGRO:00000196.label: bund
AGRO:00000196.definition: Small earth embankment which contain irrigation water within basins.

AGRO:00000420.label: column
AGRO:00000420.definition: Vertical arrangement of plants in a field.

AGRO:00000360.label: experimental site
AGRO:00000360.definition: Location where the experiment is implemented.

AGRO:00000156.label: interrow
AGRO:00000156.definition: A site which is located between two rows of crop plants.

AGRO:00000309.label: pot
AGRO:00000309.definition: A rounded container used to cultivate plant.

AGRO:00000155.label: row
AGRO:00000155.definition: two or more crop plants planted in a line.

ENVO:01000772.label: rural area
ENVO:01000772.definition: An area which is outside of a town, city, or urban area. Rural areas are primarily used for agriculture or pastoralism and may contain rural settlements.

ENVO:00001999.label: marine water body
ENVO:00001999.definition: A significant accumulation of water which is part of a marine biome.

ENVO:01000655.label: explosive eruption
ENVO:01000655.definition: An explosive eruption is a volcanic process in which pressurised magma is violently expelled and froths into volcanic ash. Explosive eruptions can eject a cloud of rocks, dust, gas, and pyroclastic material  which may then collapse, creating a pyroclastic flow of hot volcanic matter.

ENVO:01000638.label: planetary crust
ENVO:01000638.definition: A planetary crust is the outermost solid shell of a rocky planet or natural satellite, which is chemically distinct from the underlying mantle.

ENVO:01000815.label: liquid environmental material
ENVO:01000815.definition: An environmental material which is in a liquid state.

ENVO:00000303.label: sea coast
ENVO:00000303.definition: The general region of indefinite width that extends from the sea inland to the first major change in terrain features.

ENVO:01000624.label: hydrological condensation process
ENVO:01000624.definition: Hydrological condensation is a process in which atmospheric water vapour undergoes a phase transition from the gas phase to the liquid phase.

ENVO:01000788.label: conflagration
ENVO:01000788.definition: A fire which occurs in a large spatial area poses a risk to human life, animal life, health, and/or property.

ENVO:01000790.label: hydrocarbon flame
ENVO:01000790.definition: A flame which is produced by the combustion of hydrocarbon fuel.

ENVO:00002005.label: air
ENVO:00002005.definition: The mixture of gases (roughly (by molar content/volume: 78% nitrogen, 20.95% oxygen, 0.93% argon, 0.038% carbon dioxide, trace amounts of other gases, and a variable amount (average around 1%) of water vapor) that surrounds the planet Earth.

ENVO:01000266.label: water vapour
ENVO:01000266.definition: Water vapour is a vapour which is the gas phase of water.

ENVO:01000789.label: flame
ENVO:01000789.definition: A portion of gas which is emitted by a fire or other exothermic reaction, is of increased temperature, and typically emits light in the visible range.

ENVO:01001068.label: meteoroid
ENVO:01001068.definition: An astronomical body which is composed of rocky or metallic materials and is considerably smaller than asteroids.

ENVO:01000800.label: planet
ENVO:01000800.definition: A planet is an astronomical body orbiting a star or stellar remnant that is massive enough to be rounded by its own gravity, is not massive enough to cause thermonuclear fusion, and has cleared its neighbouring region of planetesimals.

ENVO:01001122.label: gas planet
ENVO:01001122.definition: A planet which is primarily composed of hydrogen and helium.

ENVO:01001137.label: ice planet
ENVO:01001137.definition: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by ice, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of ice.

ENVO:01001143.label: lava planet
ENVO:01001143.definition: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by lava, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of lava.

ENVO:01001136.label: ocean planet
ENVO:01001136.definition: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by water, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of water.

ENVO:01000958.label: terrestrial planet
ENVO:01000958.definition: A planet that is composed primarily of silicate rocks or metals.

ENVO:01000799.label: astronomical body
ENVO:01000799.definition: An object which is naturally occuring, bound together by gravitational or electromagnetic forces, and surrounded by space.

ENVO:00000094.label: volcanic feature
ENVO:00000094.definition: A feature associated with a volcano, an opening, or rupture, in the Earth's surface or crust, which allows hot, molten rock, ash and gases to escape from deep below the surface.

ENVO:01000817.label: biosphere
ENVO:01000817.definition: A biosphere is an environmental system which includes, as parts, all the living entities within the gravitational sphere of influence of an astronomical body, and the non-living and dead entities which they interact with.

ENVO:01000819.label: hydrosphere
ENVO:01000819.definition: An astronomical body part which is composed of the combined mass of water found on, under, and over the surface of a planet.

ENVO:01000983.label: technosphere
ENVO:01000983.definition: An environmental system which includes, as parts, all the entities which have been constructed or manufactured by humans or their technology within the gravitational sphere of influence of an astronomical body.

ENVO:01000256.label: mineral material
ENVO:01000256.definition: A mineral material is an environmental material which is primarily composed of some substance that is naturally occurring, solid and stable at room temperature, representable by a chemical formula, usually abiogenic, and that has an ordered atomic structure.

ENVO:00001995.label: rock
ENVO:00001995.definition: A rock is a naturally occurring solid aggregate of one or more minerals or mineraloids.

ENVO:00002006.label: water
ENVO:00002006.definition: An environmental material primarily composed of dihydrogen oxide in its liquid form.

ENVO:01000786.label: fire
ENVO:01000786.definition: A fire is a process whereby rapid and exothermic oxidation of a material through a combustion process releases heat, light, and other products.

ENVO:01000839.label: combustion process
ENVO:01000839.definition: Combustion or burning is a high-temperature exothermic redox chemical reaction between a fuel and an oxidant that produces oxidized, often gaseous products, in a mixture termed as smoke.

ENVO:01000703.label: hydrological precipitation process
ENVO:01000703.definition: Hydrological precipitation is a process during which any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapour is pulled to the planetary surface by gravity.

ENVO:01000996.label: construction process
ENVO:01000996.definition: An process during which natural or manufactured materials and products are processed and arranged by humans or their technology into structures.

ENVO:01000993.label: manufacturing process
ENVO:01000993.definition: A planned process during which raw or recycled materials are transformed into products for use or sale using labour and machines, tools, chemical and biological processing, or formulation.

ENVO:01001135.label: desert planet
ENVO:01001135.definition: A terrestrial planet which has a surface dominated by hot deserts.

ENVO:01000317.label: aquatic environment
ENVO:01000317.definition: An environment whose dynamics are strongly influenced by water.

ENVO:01000314.label: high osmolarity environment
ENVO:01000314.definition: A high osmolarity environment is an environment in which entities are exposed to high concentrations of solutes.

ENVO:01000305.label: high temperature environment
ENVO:01000305.definition: A high temperature environment is an environment in which material entities are exposed to increased levels of heat radiation or which have molecules or atoms moving randomly with increased levels of average kinietic energy.

ENVO:01001044.label: soil environment
ENVO:01001044.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by soil.

ENVO:01001052.label: aerosol environment
ENVO:01001052.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol.

ENVO:01001002.label: animal-associated environment
ENVO:01001002.definition: An environmental system determined by an animal.

ENVO:01001010.label: hydrometeor
ENVO:01001010.definition: A meteor which is primarily composed of water.

ENVO:01001012.label: lithometeor
ENVO:01001012.definition: A meteor which is primarily composed of rock.

ENVO:01001053.label: saline aerosol environment
ENVO:01001053.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a saline aerosol.

ENVO:01001054.label: non-saline aerosol environment
ENVO:01001054.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol with a low concentration of dissolved solutes.

ENVO:00000428.label: biome
ENVO:00000428.definition: A biome is an environmental system to which resident ecological communities have evolved adaptations.

ENVO:01001000.label: environmental system determined by an organism
ENVO:01001000.definition: An environmental system which is determined by a living organism.

ENVO:01001147.label: helium planet
ENVO:01001147.definition: A gas planet which has an atmosphere composed primarily of helium.

ENVO:01000277.label: water ice
ENVO:01000277.definition: Ice is water frozen into a solid state. It can appear transparent or opaque bluish-white color, depending on the presence of impurities or air inclusions. The addition of other materials such as soil may further alter its appearance.

ENVO:01000814.label: solid environmental material
ENVO:01000814.definition: An environmental material which is in a solid state.

ENVO:01001155.label: astrogeological gas
ENVO:01001155.definition: An astrogeological volatile which is composed primarily of chemical compounds with boiling points around those of hydrogen and helium.

ENVO:00000156.label: desert oasis
ENVO:00000156.definition: A small, isolated, fertile or green area in a desert region, usually having a spring or well.

ENVO:00000106.label: grassland
ENVO:00000106.definition: An area in which grasses (Graminae) are a significant component of the vegetation.

ENVO:01001304.label: oasis
ENVO:01001304.definition: An oasis is a vegetated area located in a desert, supplied with water from a water source which it surrounds, and surrounded by arid soil, sand, or rock.

ENVO:00000112.label: tundra
ENVO:00000112.definition: Treeless, level, or gently rolling plains characteristic of arctic or subarctic regions, having a permanently frozen subsoil, and usually supporting low growing vegetation such as lichens, mosses, and stunted shrubs.

ENVO:00000043.label: wetland
ENVO:00000043.definition: An area that is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances do support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions.
ENVO:00000043.synonyms: WETLAND;Wetland;wetland;mud flat;slash;back marsh;peatland;floating marsh;marsh;slue;bog;blanket bog;backswamp;mire;TerrestialWetland;dismal;quaking bog;PalustrineWetland;everglade;quagmire;barrier flat;forested wetland;MarineWetland;RiparianWetland;cienaga;slough;swamp forest;tulelands;EstuarineWetland;LacustrineWetland;backwater;peat cutting area;riparian area

ENVO:00000109.label: woodland
ENVO:00000109.definition: Land having a cover of trees, shrubs, or both.

ENVO:02000054.label: bone meal
ENVO:02000054.definition: A mixture of crushed and coarsely ground bones that is used as an organic fertilizer for plants and formerly in animal feed.

ENVO:02500027.label: anthropogenic environmental process
ENVO:02500027.definition: An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans.

ENVO:02500003.label: atmospheric process
ENVO:02500003.definition: A process which occurs within an atmosphere.

ENVO:02500001.label: desertification
ENVO:02500001.definition: a type of land degradation in which a relatively dry land region becomes increasingly arid, typically losing its bodies of water as well as vegetation and wildlife.

ENVO:1000748.label: island formation process
ENVO:1000748.definition: A process which results in the formation of an island.

ENVO:03000009.label: material accumulation process
ENVO:03000009.definition: A process during which the mass of one or more materials, present within a given site, increases.

ENVO:03000043.label: material transformation process
ENVO:03000043.definition: A process during which a portion of some environmental material is converted into a different material or a collection of materials.

ENVO:03000010.label: material transport process
ENVO:03000010.definition: A process during which material is displaced from it's original location and transported either to a new location or back to the original location.

ENVO:01001023.label: radiation
ENVO:01001023.definition: A process during which energy is emitted or transmitted in the form of waves or particles through space or a material medium.

ENVO:01000705.label: soil degradation
ENVO:01000705.definition: Soil degradation is a process which results in a change in soil health status resulting in a diminished capacity of the ecosystem in which the soil occurs to provide goods and services for its  beneficiaries.

ENVO:01000952.label: anthropisation
ENVO:01000952.definition: A process during which a natural environmental system is altered by human action.

ENVO:01000706.label: soil erosion
ENVO:01000706.definition: Soil erosion is a process in which exogenic processes remove soil from one location on the Earth's crust and transport it to another location where it is deposited.

ENVO:02500002.label: flooding
ENVO:02500002.definition: A general and temporary condition of partial or complete inundation of normally dry land areas from the overflow of inland and/or tidal waters, and/or the unusual and rapid accumulation or runoff of surface waters from any source. A great flow along a watercourse or a flow causing inundation of lands not normally covered by water.

AGRO:00000199.label: percolation process in soil
AGRO:00000199.definition: Hydrological process in which water move through soil and permeable rocks.

ENVO:01000634.label: volcanic eruption
ENVO:01000634.definition: A volcanic process is a process during which lava, tephra (ash, lapilli, volcanic bombs and blocks), and assorted gases are expelled from a volcanic vent or fissure.

ENVO:02500028.label: erosion
ENVO:02500028.definition: An action of exogenic processes (such as water flow or wind) which remove soil and rock from one location on the Earth's crust, then transport it to another location where it is deposited.

ENVO:03000020.label: aeolian transport process
ENVO:03000020.definition: A material transport process during which one or more environmental materials are transported by the action of wind.

ENVO:01000792.label: mass gaseous flow
ENVO:01000792.definition: A process whereby a large volume of gas moves due to a disequilibrium of physical forces.
