ENVO:01000875.label: precipitation process
ENVO:01000875.definition: A precipitation process is a process in which a portion of some substance segregates from a material in which that substance or its precursors were dissolved or suspended in and settles due to a force such as gravity or centrifugal force.

ENVO:01000724.label: condensation process
ENVO:01000724.definition: Condensation is a process during which a gas undergoes a phase transition into a liquid.

GO:0051816.label: acquisition of nutrients from other organism during symbiotic interaction

OGMS:0000063.label: disease course
OGMS:0000063.definition: The totality of all processes through which a given disease instance is realized.

UO:0000051.label: concentration unit
UO:0000051.definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance.

UO:0000105.label: frequency unit
UO:0000105.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of repetitive actions in a particular time.

UO:0000001.label: length unit
UO:0000001.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

UO:0000002.label: mass unit
UO:0000002.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of matter/energy of a physical object.

UO:0000280.label: rate unit
UO:0000280.definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement occurrence of a process per unit time.

UO:0000006.label: substance unit
UO:0000006.definition: A unit which is a standardised quantity of an element or compound with uniform composition.

UO:0000005.label: temperature unit
UO:0000005.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a sample of matter.

UO:0000003.label: time unit
UO:0000003.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

UO:0000095.label: volume unit
UO:0000095.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of space occupied by any substance, whether solid, liquid, or gas.

UO:0000270.label: volumetric flow rate unit
UO:0000270.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time .

OBI:0000684.label: specimen collection objective
OBI:0000684.definition: A objective specification to obtain a material entity for potential use as an input during an investigation.

OBI:0000962.label: training objective
OBI:0000962.definition: An objective specification which is fulfilled by the provision of some training.

OBI:0000441.label: assay objective
OBI:0000441.definition: an objective specification to determine a specified type of information about an evaluated entity (the material entity bearing evaluant role)

OBI:0000015.label: biological feature identification objective
OBI:0000015.definition: Biological_feature_identification_objective is an objective role carried out by the proposition defining the aim of a study designed to examine or characterize a particular biological feature.

OBI:0200166.label: data transformation objective
OBI:0200166.definition: An objective specification to transformation input data into output data

OBI:0000456.label: material transformation objective
OBI:0000456.definition: an objective specifiction that creates an specific output object from input materials.

OBI:0001175.label: selective organism creation objective
OBI:0001175.definition: an objective specification to generate a population or type of organism within species that have some uniform behavioral, morphological, physiological, or genetic characteristics with similarly bred organisms.

OBI:0000963.label: categorical label
OBI:0000963.definition: A label that is part of a categorical datum and that indicates the value of the data item on the categorical scale.

IAO:0000003.label: measurement unit label
IAO:0000003.definition: A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

OBI:0000713.label: GenePattern software
OBI:0000713.definition: a software that provides access to more than 100 tools for gene expression analysis, proteomics, SNP analysis and common data processing tasks.

OBI:0000679.label: average value
OBI:0000679.definition: A  data item that is produced as the output of an averaging data transformation and represents the average value of the input data.

OBI:0000674.label: center value
OBI:0000674.definition: A data item that is produced as the output of a center calculation data transformation and represents the center value of the input data.

IAO:0000102.label: data about an ontology part
IAO:0000102.definition: data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

IAO:0000100.label: data set
IAO:0000100.definition: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

IAO:0000109.label: measurement datum
IAO:0000109.definition: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

OBI:0001909.label: conclusion based on data
OBI:0001909.definition: An information content entity that is inferred from data.

OBI:0001933.label: value specification
OBI:0001933.definition: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.

IAO:0000027.label: data item
IAO:0000027.definition: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

IAO:0000009.label: datum label
IAO:0000009.definition: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

IAO:0000033.label: directive information entity
IAO:0000033.definition: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

IAO:0000310.label: document
IAO:0000310.definition: A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

IAO:0000308.label: figure
IAO:0000308.definition: An information content entity consisting of a two dimensional arrangement of information content entities such that the arrangement itself is about something.

OBI:0001554.label: rate measurement datum
OBI:0001554.definition: A scalar measurement datum that represents the number of events occuring over a time interval

IAO:0000408.label: length measurement datum
IAO:0000408.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of length quality

IAO:0000414.label: mass measurement datum
IAO:0000414.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of mass quality

IAO:0000416.label: time measurement datum
IAO:0000416.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

OBI:0000969.label: dose specification
OBI:0000969.definition: a directive information entity that describes the dose that will be administered to a target

IAO:0000007.label: action specification
IAO:0000007.definition: a directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take

IAO:0000098.label: data format specification
IAO:0000098.definition:
A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.
Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file

IAO:0000005.label: objective specification
IAO:0000005.definition: a directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

IAO:0000104.label: plan specification
IAO:0000104.definition: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

OBI:0000750.label: study design independent variable
OBI:0000750.definition: a directive information entity that is part of a study design. Independent variables are entities whose values are selected to determine its relationship to an observed phenomenon (the dependent variable). In such an experiment, an attempt is made to find evidence that the values of the independent variable determine the values of the dependent variable (that which is being measured). The independent variable can be changed as required, and its values do not represent a problem requiring explanation in an analysis, but are taken simply as given. The dependent variable on the other hand, usually cannot be directly controlled

IAO:0000183.label: dendrogram
IAO:0000183.definition:
A dendrogram is a report graph which is a tree diagram
frequently used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by a
clustering algorithm.

IAO:0000037.label: dot plot
IAO:0000037.definition: A dot plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where each data point is represented by a single dot placed on coordinates corresponding to data point values in particular dimensions.

IAO:0000180.label: heatmap
IAO:0000180.definition:
A heatmap is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data
where the values taken by a variable(s) are shown as colors in a
two-dimensional map.

IAO:0000179.label: histogram
IAO:0000179.definition:
A histogram is a report graph which is a statistical description of a
distribution in terms of occurrence frequencies of different event classes.

IAO:0000184.label: scatter plot
IAO:0000184.definition: A scatterplot is a graph which uses Cartesian coordinates to display values for two variables for a set of data. The data is displayed as a collection of points, each having the value of one variable determining the position on the horizontal axis and the value of the other variable determining the position on the vertical axis.

OBI:0000023.label: classified data set
OBI:0000023.definition: A data set that is produced as the output of a class prediction data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned class labels.

OBI:0000648.label: clustered data set
OBI:0000648.definition: A data set that is produced as the output of a class discovery data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned discovered class labels.

IAO:0000409.label: denotator type
IAO:0000409.definition: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

IAO:0000078.label: curation status specification
IAO:0000078.definition: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

IAO:0000225.label: obsolescence reason specification
IAO:0000225.definition: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

IAO:0000064.label: algorithm
IAO:0000064.definition: A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.

AGRO:00000036.label: application method
AGRO:00000036.definition: A plan specification which describes how a material entity is applied to another material entity.

AGRO:00000054.label: irrigation method
AGRO:00000054.definition: A plan specification which describes how water is applied to plants or soil.

AGRO:00000350.label: planting distribution
AGRO:00000350.definition: Pattern used to plant crop in field.

OBI:0000272.label: protocol
OBI:0000272.definition: A plan specification which has sufficient level of detail and quantitative information to communicate it between investigation agents, so that different investigation agents will reliably be able to independently reproduce the process.

IAO:0000010.label: software
IAO:0000010.definition:
Software is a plan specification composed of a series of instructions that can be 
interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.

OBI:0500000.label: study design
OBI:0500000.definition: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

OBI:0001620.label: latitude coordinate measurement datum
OBI:0001620.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.

OBI:0001621.label: longitude coordinate measurement datum
OBI:0001621.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.

IAO:0000032.label: scalar measurement datum
IAO:0000032.definition: a scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

IAO:0000309.label: diagram
IAO:0000309.definition: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

IAO:0000101.label: image
IAO:0000101.definition: An image is an affine projection to a two dimensional surface, of measurements of some quality of an entity or entities repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, where the measurements are represented as color and luminosity on the projected on surface.

IAO:0000038.label: graph
IAO:0000038.definition: A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

OBI:0001000.label: questionnaire
OBI:0001000.definition: A document with a set of printed or written questions with a choice of answers, devised for the purposes of a survey or statistical study.

OBI:0001167.label: age measurement datum
OBI:0001167.definition: A time measurement datum that is the result of measurement of age of an organism

OBI:0000659.label: specimen collection process
OBI:0000659.definition: A planned process with the objective of collecting a specimen.

OBI:0000471.label: study design execution
OBI:0000471.definition: a planned process that carries out a study design

OBI:0000931.label: study intervention
OBI:0000931.definition: the part of the execution of an intervention design study which is varied between two or more subjects in the study

OBI:0000939.label: training process
OBI:0000939.definition: a process that achieves a training objective

AGRO:01000000.label: agronomic fertilization process
AGRO:01000000.definition: A planned process in which fertilizer is applied to an environmental material to promote the growth of a plant.

OBI:0000070.label: assay
OBI:0000070.definition: A planned process with the objective to produce information about the material entity that is the evaluant, by physically examining it or its proxies.

AGRO:01000020.label: crop cultivation process
AGRO:01000020.definition: A planned process during which the environment of a crop plant is maintained such that the plant grows

AGRO:00000005.label: crop residue management process
AGRO:00000005.definition: A planned process in which the thickness of crop residue on the surface of an agricultural field is managed.

OBI:0200000.label: data transformation
OBI:0200000.definition: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

OBI:0200111.label: data visualization
OBI:0200111.definition: An planned process that creates images, diagrams or animations from the input data.

IAO:0000572.label: documenting
IAO:0000572.definition: a planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.

OBI:0000338.label: drawing a conclusion based on data
OBI:0000338.definition: A planned process in which data gathered in an investigation is evaluated in the context of existing knowledge with the objective to generate more general conclusions or to conclude that the data does not allow one to draw general conclusion

AGRO:00000369.label: experiment
AGRO:00000369.definition: A planned process in which a procedure is carried out to support, refute, or validate a hypothesis.

AGRO:00000025.label: harvesting process
AGRO:00000025.definition: A planned process in which the useful part or parts of the plant are gathered.

OBI:0000066.label: investigation
OBI:0000066.definition: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

AGRO:00000006.label: irrigation process
AGRO:00000006.definition: A planned process in which water is artificially supplied to plant or soil to sustain plants.

AGRO:00000004.label: land levelling process
AGRO:00000004.definition: A planned process in which the agricultural field surface is shaped for ensuring that the depths and discharge variations over the agricultural field are relatively uniform.

AGRO:00000112.label: liming process
AGRO:00000112.definition: A planned process in which a liming material is applied to soil to reduce acidity.

OBI:0000094.label: material processing
OBI:0000094.definition: A planned process which results in physical changes in a specified input material

AGRO:00000023.label: pest control process
AGRO:00000023.definition: A planned process in which unwanted organisms are controlled.

AGRO:00000229.label: plant transplanting process
AGRO:00000229.definition: A planned process in which a plant is moved from one location to be planted in another one.

AGRO:00000231.label: planting process
AGRO:00000231.definition: A planned process in which a plant reproductive material is set into the soil.

AGRO:00000461.label: propping process
AGRO:00000461.definition: A planned process in which a rigid support is used to support, or to prevent from falling a crop or a tree.

AGRO:00000027.label: pruning process
AGRO:00000027.definition: A planned process in which selected parts of the plant are removed. The practice entails targeted removal of diseased, damaged, dead, non-productive, structurally unsound, or otherwise unwanted tissue from plants. This is done in order to shape the plant or tree, improve plant or tree health, reduce the risk from falling branches, prepare nursery specimens for transplanting, and increase the yield or quality of harvested products.

AGRO:00000426.label: regulation of grazing
AGRO:00000426.definition: A planned process in which grazing animals on pasture are managed by humans.

AGRO:00000349.label: soil analysis process
AGRO:00000349.definition: A planned process in which an analysis of soil is performed to determine soil characteristics.

AGRO:00000322.label: treatment
AGRO:00000322.definition: A process during which some material is applied to a subject

OBI:0000268.label: organism feature identification objective
OBI:0000268.definition: Organism_feature_identification_objective is a biological_feature_identification_objective role describing a study designed to examine or characterize a biological feature monitored at the level of the organism, e.g. height, weight, stage of development, stage of life cycle.

OBI:0000014.label: regulator role
OBI:0000014.definition: a regulatory role involved with making and/or enforcing relevant legislation and governmental orders

OBI:0000953.label: processed specimen
OBI:0000953.definition: A specimen that has been intentionally physically modified.

OBI:0000944.label: handedness assay
OBI:0000944.definition: A handedness assay measures the unequal distribution of fine motor skill between the left and right hands typically in human subjects by means of some questionnaire and scoring procedure.

OBI:0001158.label: age measurement assay
OBI:0001158.definition: An assay that measures the duration of temporal interval of a process that is part of the life of the bearer, where the initial time point of the measured process is the beginning of some transitional state of the bearer such as birth or when planted.

OBI:0000652.label: material combination
OBI:0000652.definition: is a material processing with the objective to combine two or more material entities as input into a single material entity as output.

OBI:0000457.label: manufacturing
OBI:0000457.definition: Manufacturing is a process with the intent to produce a processed material which will have a function for future use. A person or organization (having manufacturer role) is a participant in this process

OBI:0000828.label: research organization
OBI:0000828.definition: An organization formed with a goal to have its members conduct investigations

OBI:0001942.label: grant agency
OBI:0001942.definition: An organization that provides funding support for projects such as investigations.

OBI:0000450.label: regulatory agency
OBI:0000450.definition: A regulatory agency is a organization that has responsibility over or for  the legislation (acts and regulations) for a given sector of the government.

AGRO:00000255.label: agricultural process depth measurement protocol
AGRO:00000255.definition: Measurement protocol in which the depth into the soil of an agricultural process is measured.

AGRO:00000286.label: area measurement protocol
AGRO:00000286.definition: Protocol that describes how to measure a field area.

AGRO:00000252.label: bund height measurement protocol
AGRO:00000252.definition: Measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of a bund. Repeat this operation on multiple bunds, and average the results.

AGRO:00000258.label: chemical concentration in fertilizer recording protocol
AGRO:00000258.definition: Record the concentration of the chemical element of interest in the fertilizer used indicated on the fertilizer container.

AGRO:00000275.label: determination of organic carbon protocol
AGRO:00000275.definition: Protocol used to determine the content of organic carbon in environmental material.

AGRO:00000274.label: determination of organic nitrogen in environmental material protocol
AGRO:00000274.definition: Protocol used to determine the content of organic nitrogen in environmental material.

AGRO:00000295.label: environmental material incorporation percentage measurement protocol
AGRO:00000295.definition: Protocol that describes how to measure the percentage of incorporation in soil of an environmental material.

AGRO:00000259.label: harvested row counting protocol
AGRO:00000259.definition: Count the number of row that have been harvested.

AGRO:00000248.label: interrow width measurement protocol
AGRO:00000248.definition: With a ruler measure the distance between the center of two rows. The center of the rows is where the plant reproductive material has been planted.

AGRO:00000280.label: irrigation equipment depth measurement protocol
AGRO:00000280.definition: Measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of the irrigation equipment buried in soil.

AGRO:00000284.label: irrigation water quantity recording protocol
AGRO:00000284.definition: Record the quantity of water used for irrigation.

AGRO:00000264.label: lignin concentration measurement protocol
AGRO:00000264.definition: Protocol in which the lignin concentration of an environmental material is measured.

AGRO:00000242.label: material area density mesurement protocol
AGRO:00000242.definition: Protocol used to measure the area density of a material.

AGRO:00000251.label: moisture concentration measurement protocol
AGRO:00000251.definition: 1.Weight a sample of the material. 2.Dry this sample. 3.Weight the dry sample. Moisture concentration = ((Ww-Wd)/Ww) x 100 in which : WW = wet weight of the sample, and Wd = weight of the sample after drying.

AGRO:00000278.label: mulch color recording protocol
AGRO:00000278.definition: Record the color of the mulch applied.

AGRO:00000247.label: mulch thickness measurement protocol
AGRO:00000247.definition: With a ruler measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of the mulch layer.

AGRO:00000449.label: nitrogen recovery efficiency measurement protocol
AGRO:00000449.definition: Calculate the amount of nitrogen in the crop as a ratio of the amount of nitrogen applied or available.

AGRO:00000451.label: nitrogen use efficiency measurement protocol
AGRO:00000451.definition: Calculate the ratio between the amount of nitrogen fertilizer removed with the crop and the amount of nitrogen fertilizer applied.

AGRO:00000285.label: percolation test protocol
AGRO:00000285.definition: Protocol in which the rapidity at which water moves through soil is measured.

AGRO:00000283.label: pest control agent released density recording protocol
AGRO:00000283.definition: Record the number of pest control agent released per surface area.

AGRO:00000282.label: pivot lenght measurement protocol
AGRO:00000282.definition: Measure the lenght of the pivot.

AGRO:00000262.label: plant density measurement protocol
AGRO:00000262.definition: Protocol that describes how to count the number of plants in a known area.

AGRO:00000263.label: row length mesurement protocol
AGRO:00000263.definition: Measure the distance between the beginning and the end of the row.

AGRO:00000290.label: soil coverage by environmental material measurement protocol
AGRO:00000290.definition: Protocol that describes how to measure the percentage of soil coverage by environmental material like mulch or crop residue.

AGRO:00000249.label: sprout lenght measurement protocol
AGRO:00000249.definition: Measure the length of sprout with a steel tape.

AGRO:00000294.label: total quantity of environmental material used compute protocol
AGRO:00000294.definition: Add all the quantities of the environmental material of interest applied over a specified period.

AGRO:00000277.label: tractor speed recording protocol
AGRO:00000277.definition: Record the speed of the tractor in the field.

AGRO:00000279.label: transplant age counting protocol
AGRO:00000279.definition: Protocol in which the age of the transplant is determined by counting the number of days between the seeding date and the transplanting date.

AGRO:00000250.label: water source distance measurement protocol
AGRO:00000250.definition: Measure the shortest distance between the water source and the entrance of the field with a measuring wheel.

AGRO:00000281.label: well depth measurement protocol
AGRO:00000281.definition: Tie a small but heavy weight to the end of a piece of string. Lower the weight into the well until it reaches the bottom. Take up the slack and mark the string at ground level. Pull the weight out of the well and measure from the bottom of the weight to the ground level mark. This is the depth of the well.

OBI:0600007.label: administering substance in vivo
OBI:0600007.definition: A process by which a substance is intentionally given to an organism resulting in exposure of the organism to that substance.

OBI:0000686.label: material combination objective
OBI:0000686.definition: is an objective to obtain an output material that contains several input materials.

OBI:0001153.label: genetic transformation objective
OBI:0001153.definition: a material transformation objective aims to create genetically modified organism or cell

OBI:0000458.label: manufacturing objective
OBI:0000458.definition: is the objective to manufacture a material of a certain function (device)

OBI:0000274.label: adding a material entity into a target
OBI:0000274.definition: is a process with the objective to place a material entity bearing the 'material to be added role' into a material bearing the 'target of material addition role'.

OBI:0000700.label: support vector machine
OBI:0000700.definition: A support vector machine is a data transformation with a class prediction objective based on the construction of a separating hyperplane that maximizes the margin between two data sets of vectors in n-dimensional space.

OBI:0000434.label: adding material objective
OBI:0000434.definition: is the specification of an objective to add a material into a target material. The adding is asymmetric in the sense that the target material largely retains its identity

OBI:0000749.label: CART
OBI:0000749.definition: A CART (classification and regression trees) is a data transformation method for producing a classification or regression model with a tree-based structure.

OBI:0200033.label: leave one out cross validation method
OBI:0200033.definition: is a data transformation :  leave-one-out cross-validation (LOOCV) involves using a single observation from the original sample as the validation data, and the remaining observations as the training data. This is repeated such that each observation in the sample is used once as the validation data

OBI:0000018.label: material supplier role
OBI:0000018.definition: a role realized through the process of supplying materials such as animal subjects, reagents or other materials used in an investigation.

OBI:0302716.label: pool of specimens
OBI:0302716.definition: A pool of specimens is a mixture of a population of samples which have been gathered from one or more sample populations, obtained by the physical process of mixing individual specimens, e.g.  mixing the DNA collected from the individual fish.

OBI:0001161.label: age since germination measurement datum
OBI:0001161.definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since germination, the process consisting of physiological and developmental changes by a seed, spore, pollen grain (microspore), or zygote that occur after release from dormancy, and encompassing events prior to and including the first visible indications of growth.

OBI:0001156.label: age since planting measurement datum
OBI:0001156.definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since planting, the process of placing a plant in media (e.g. soil) to allow it to grow, which excludes sowing.

OBI:0001164.label: age since sowing measurement datum
OBI:0001164.definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since sowing, the process of placing a seed or spore in some media with the intention to invoke germination.

OBI:0002326.label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification
OBI:0002326.definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a gynecologic cancer according to the International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) staging systems.

OBI:0002341.label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification
OBI:0002341.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the FIGO classification system.

OBI:0002314.label: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002314.definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) v7 staging systems.

OBI:0002205.label: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002205.definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) 7th Edition grading system.

OBI:0002210.label: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System

AGRO:00000325.label: crop
AGRO:00000325.definition: A crop is any cultivated plant, fungus, or alga that is harvested for food, clothing, livestock,fodder, biofuel, medicine, or other uses

AGRO:00000116.label: draft animal
AGRO:00000116.definition: Organism used to pull agricultural implements.

OBI:0001185.label: selectively maintained organism
OBI:0001185.definition: An organism that is bred to have some uniform behavioral, morphological, physiological, or genetic characteristics with similarly bred organisms

OBI:0000726.label: peak matching
OBI:0000726.definition: Peak matching is a data transformation performed on a dataset of a graph of ordered data points (e.g. a spectrum) with the objective of pattern matching local maxima above a noise threshold

OBI:0200170.label: averaging data transformation
OBI:0200170.definition: An averaging data transformation is a data transformation that has objective averaging.

OBI:0200181.label: center calculation data transformation
OBI:0200181.definition: A center calculation data transformation is a data transformation that has objective of center calculation.

OBI:0200175.label: class discovery data transformation
OBI:0200175.definition: A class discovery data transformation (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class discovery.

OBI:0000663.label: class prediction data transformation
OBI:0000663.definition: A class prediction data transformation (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class prediction.

OBI:0000707.label: decision tree building data transformation
OBI:0000707.definition: A decision tree building data transformation is a data transformation that has objective decision tree induction.

OBI:0200171.label: partitioning data transformation
OBI:0200171.definition: A partitioning data transformation is a data transformation that has objective partitioning.

OBI:0200051.label: principal components analysis dimensionality reduction
OBI:0200051.definition: A principal components analysis dimensionality reduction is a dimensionality reduction achieved by applying principal components analysis and by keeping low-order principal components and excluding higher-order ones.

OBI:0200190.label: clustered data visualization
OBI:0200190.definition: A data visualization which has input of a clustered data set and produces an output of a report graph which is capable of rendering data of this type.

OBI:0000704.label: decision tree induction objective
OBI:0000704.definition: A decision tree induction objective is a data transformation objective in which a tree-like graph of edges and nodes is created and from which the selection of each branch requires that some type of logical decision is made.

OBI:0000425.label: averaging objective
OBI:0000425.definition: An averaging objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to perform mean calculations on the input of the data transformation.

OBI:0200177.label: center calculation objective
OBI:0200177.definition: A center calculation objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to calculate the center of an input data set.

OBI:0200178.label: class discovery objective
OBI:0200178.definition: A class discovery objective (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to organize input data  (typically vectors of attributes) into classes, where the number of classes and their specifications are not known a priori. Depending on usage, the class assignment can be definite or probabilistic.

OBI:0200179.label: class prediction objective
OBI:0200179.definition:
A class prediction objective (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to create a predictor from training data through a machine learning technique. The training data consist of pairs of objects (typically vectors of attributes) and
class labels for these objects. The resulting predictor can be used to attach class labels to any valid novel input object. Depending on usage, the prediction can be definite or probabilistic. A classification is learned from the training data and can then be tested on test data.

OBI:0200172.label: partitioning objective
OBI:0200172.definition: A partitioning objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to generate a collection of disjoint non-empty subsets whose union equals a non-empty input set.

OBI:0000792.label: statistical model validation
OBI:0000792.definition: A data transformation which assesses how the results of a statistical analysis will generalize to an independent data set.

OBI:0200041.label: k-means clustering
OBI:0200041.definition: A k-means clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, which takes as input a collection of objects (represented as points in multidimensional space) and which partitions them into a specified number k of clusters. The algorithm attempts to find the centers of natural clusters in the data. The most common form of the algorithm starts by partitioning the input points into k initial sets, either at random or using some heuristic data. It then calculates the mean point, or centroid, of each set. It constructs a new partition by associating each point with the closest centroid. Then the centroids are recalculated for the new clusters, and the algorithm repeated by alternate applications of these two steps until convergence, which is obtained when the points no longer switch clusters (or alternatively centroids are no longer changed).

OBI:0000727.label: k-nearest neighbors
OBI:0000727.definition: A k-nearest neighbors is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, in which an input data object with vector y is assigned to a class label based upon the k closest training data set points to y; where k is the largest value that class label is assigned.

OBI:0200188.label: cross validation objective
OBI:0200188.definition: A cross validation objective is a data transformation objective in which the aim is to partition a sample of data into subsets such that the analysis is initially performed on a single subset, while the other subset(s) are retained for subsequent use in confirming and validating the initial analysis.

OBI:0200050.label: dimensionality reduction
OBI:0200050.definition: A dimensionality reduction is data partitioning which transforms each input m-dimensional vector (x_1, x_2, ..., x_m) into an output n-dimensional vector (y_1, y_2, ..., y_n), where n is smaller than m.

OBI:0200042.label: hierarchical clustering
OBI:0200042.definition: A hierarchical clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery objective, which takes as input data item and builds a hierarchy of clusters. The traditional representation of this hierarchy is a tree (visualized by a dendrogram), with the individual input objects at one end (leaves) and a single cluster containing every object at the other (root).

AGRO:00000343.label: agronomic experimental design
AGRO:00000343.definition: A plan specification that states how treatments are allocated to the experimental units during an agronomic trial. It refers to the conceptual framework within which the experiment is conducted.

OBI:0001293.label: disease state design
OBI:0001293.definition: A study design in which the pathological condition of a part, organ, or system of an organism is studied. The etiology may be from infection, genetic defect, or environmental stress.

OBI:0000115.label: intervention design
OBI:0000115.definition: An intervention design is a study design in which a controlled process applied to the subjects (the intervention) serves as the independent variable manipulated by the experimentalist. The treatment (perturbation or intervention) defined can be defined as a combination of values taken by independent variable manipulated by the experimentalists are applied to the recruited subjects assigned (possibly by applying specific methods) to treatment groups. The specificity of intervention design is the fact that independent variables are being manipulated and a response of the biological system is evaluated via response variables as monitored by possibly a series of assays.

OBI:0001464.label: strain comparison design
OBI:0001464.definition: A study design that assays differences between multiple strains, cultivars, serovars, isolates, lines from organisms of a single species.

OBI:0500011.label: latin square design
OBI:0500011.definition: Latin square design is_a study design which allows in its simpler form controlling 2 levels of nuisance variables (also known as blocking variables).he 2 nuisance factors are divided into a tabular grid with the property that each row and each column receive each treatment exactly once.

PATO:0000060.label: spatial pattern

PATO:0001502.definition: A monadic quality of continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

PATO:0000025.label: composition
PATO:0000025.definition: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts.

PATO:0002124.label: laminar
PATO:0002124.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

PATO:0000970.label: permeability

PATO:0001442.label: wholeness

ENVO:09200000.definition: The temperature of some environmental material.

PATO:0002201.label: handedness

PATO:0001701.label: mature

PATO:0000963.label: opaque
PATO:0000963.definition: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being clear; not transmitting or reflecting light or radiant energy.

PATO:0000973.label: porosity

PATO:0000984.label: porous
PATO:0000984.definition: A porosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

PATO:0001585.label: conductivity
PATO:0001585.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

PATO:0000039.label: direction

PATO:0000040.label: distance

PATO:0001019.label: mass density

PATO:0001906.label: movement quality
PATO:0001906.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's participation in movement.

PATO:0000140.label: position

PATO:0001025.label: pressure

PATO:0001470.label: proportionality to
PATO:0001470.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude in respect to a related entity.

PATO:0002198.label: quality of a substance
PATO:0002198.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

PATO:0001739.label: radiation quality
PATO:0001739.definition: A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.

PATO:0000085.label: sensitivity toward
PATO:0000085.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to detect or perceive external stimulation.

PATO:0000146.label: temperature
PATO:0000146.definition: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.

PATO:0000165.label: time

PATO:0001822.label: wetness

PATO:0001026.label: work

PATO:0001351.label: area density

PATO:0001352.label: linear density

ENVO:09200005.label: mass density of soil

PATO:0001353.label: volumetric density

PATO:0000186.label: behavioral quality

PATO:0002303.label: decreased object quality
